<IMG SRC="/rsc/photow8.gif" ALT="= CESD  Home Page ="></A>  
</P>
<H2>Sustainable Community Codes and Ordinances</H2>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
</P>
<P>      Building sustainable communities requires that local citizens make
decisions on a variety of practical issues, including open space access,
building quality, energy performance, land-use patterns and many others. Once
these difficult decisions are made, communities must codify many of them in
codes, ordinances, policy statements and other legal tools.       
</P>
<P>We are gathering the codes, ordinances, and policy statements developed by
communities that are already implementing sustainable development programs. They
are produced here verbatim so they can serve as models, if not actual text, for
other communities whose sustainable development initiatives are just beginning.</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER>
<P><BR>
</P>
<DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="/rsc/mball.gif" ALT=" * "> 
