</P> 
<P><BR CLEAR="all"></P>
<H2>Sustainability Success Stories</H2>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif" ALT=" "></CENTER>
<P></P>
<P>
 Sustainable development is not just a theoretical concept.  Large  cities and
rural communities across the United States have already  put these principles to
work, proving that economic development and  environmentally and socially
healthy communities can coexist.  The Center of Excellence for Sustainable
Development commissioned two organizations -- Public Technology, Inc. and Renew
America -- to gather information on how these communities and organizations made
sustainable development work for them.  We've highlighted  several dozen of
these successful and innovative  approaches to sustainable community
development.   </P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/rsc/mball.gif" ALT=" * ">
<A HREF="/ss/success.html">
<B>Renew America - Sustainable Success Stories</B></A>
</P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/rsc/mball.gif" ALT=" * ">
<A HREF="/ss/pti/index.html">
<B>Public Technology Incorporated - Sustainable Success Stories</B></A>
</P>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER>
</P>
<P><A HREF="/index.html"><IMG ALIGN="BOTTOM" SRC="/rsc/left_arr.gif"></A></P>
