<H1>Slide Shows</H1>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><BR> 
</P>
<P><BR> We've created two online slide shows that show outstanding  examples
of community sustainability in both rural and urban settings.  Click on the
links below to see these shows.  Each slide will be presented in a reduced view,
but can be enlarged by clicking on the reduced image.  Be aware that it can take
awhile to download graphics files.</P>
<P>
 We've also produced  a  fifteen-minute video that captures the highlights of
sustainable community development in the United States.  This video, titled &quot;Creating
Communities That Work,&quot; is an excellent tool to help introduce your
community to the principles of sustainable development.</P>
<P>
 To request your free copy of the sustainable development  video, call, write,
or fax  the Center of Excellence at the address below, or click on the e-mail
address and send a request with your name, address, organization, and phone
number.</P>
<ADDRESS>Center of Excellence for Sustainable Development<BR>
U.S. Department of Energy<BR>
Office of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy<BR>
Denver Regional Support Office<BR>
1617 Cole Boulevard<BR>
Golden, CO 80401<BR>
Toll Free Phone: 800/357-7732<BR>
Fax: 303/275-4830<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:sustainable.development@hq.doe.gov"><B>sustainable.development@hq.doe.gov </B>
</A>
</ADDRESS>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><BR> 
</P>
