<P><BR CLEAR="all"><BR></P>
<H2>Sustainability Success Stories  from Renew America</H2>

<!-- ------------------------------------------------------updated 11-15-96 ct ---------------------------------------->
<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif" ALT=" "><BR>
</P></CENTER>

<P>   The following communities and organizations have been selected as
outstanding examples of sustainable development in action from Renew America's &quot;Environmental
Success Index.&quot;   Renew America, a Washington DC nonprofit organization,
has developed a rigorous data collection and verification program to select some
of most innovative sustainable development programs in the United States.  
</P>
<P>Projects selected for inclusion in this list were evaluated by an
independent group of nonprofit organizations.  In addition, each nominee 
submitted the names of five references, two of whom must be nonprofit
organizations.  Applications were judged on the basis of program effectiveness,
human development, natural resource conservation, and economic progress.</P>
<P>For more information, call <B>202-232-2252</B>, or go to their website at
<A HREF="http://solstice.crest.org/environment/renew_america/index.html"><B>http://solstice.crest.org/environment/renew_america</B></A>.</P>

