<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/62.gif"><img src="t/62.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> The "Proposal for a Quality Environment" had suggested Indian Brook could be used for "boating, fishing, picnicking, camping, nature trails and scenic overlooks." Although the Essex Village Board of Trustees had sold the reservoir area in 1977 to a consortium of developers, the Friends of Indian Brook fought on for its acquisition and preservation and eventually prevailed. A bond vote allocated $750,000 for purchase of the property and related improvements. The Nature Conservancy donated an additional $16,000 toward the purchase. Today, Indian Brook Park is a recreational mecca for area residents, who fish, canoe, hike, bird-watch, picnic, cross-country ski and skate.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "61.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "63.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/62.html</h5></body></html>
