<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/39.gif"><img src="t/39.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> RuralAction has organized a Sustainable Grazing project, which promotes controlled grazing practices. In addition, its Agriculture Education project will develop a sustainable agriculture curriculum for use in elementary school, high school, and adult vocational agricultural programs. AmeriCorps VISTA has promised to cover direct costs of the projects' organizers, but additional funding is being sought for a part-time pasture specialist and other assistance.	In the gathering depicted, local farmers join Rick Duff for a discussion about sustainable agriculture.	 According to RuralAction, many farmers in Southeast Ohio have trouble making ends meet. "Conventional agricultural practices deplete topsoil, are capital intensive, cause environmental damage and result in low profits."<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "38.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "40.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</