<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/16.gif"><img src="t/16.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> In an article about Farmview for The Urban Land Institute, Arendt noted: "At Farmview, 332 single-family houses are being built on just half of the land they would ordinarily have consumed, while 213 acres of fields and forests are being preserved at no cost to the community, the original landowner, or the developer."Lot sizes were reduced from one acre to one-half or one-third acre, preserving more than half the parcel in permanent open space. In 1993, Arendt reported that Farmview was "the fastest selling development in its price range in Bucks County." And, he noted, "Market surveys indicate that homebuyers are attracted to rural Bucks County by its farm fields, woodland habitats, and appealing country character...Key factors in Farmview's success have been the homesites' proximity to and views of the open spaces."<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "15.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "17.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/16.html</h5></body></html>
