<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/41.gif"><img src="t/41.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> RuralAction is involved also in another collaborative effort - the Monday Creek Restoration Project. Here, local officials and project coordinators view acid mine drainage damage during a Monday Creek Restoration Project field day.Because of pollution related to acidic drainage from abandoned mines, Monday Creek is devoid of life. Its restoration will require an enormous expenditure of time, effort and money. But the watershed work is beginning, one of RuralAction's many "sustainable" efforts.<p>In Idaho, The Henry's Fork Foundation is working to save a different watershed - the Henry's Fork of the Snake River.			<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "40.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "42.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/41.html</h5></body></html>
