<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/76.gif"><img src="t/76.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**-->	<I>"The sustainability of our communities cannot be legislated in Washington. Local government and the people are in the best position to preserve the uniqueness of each community."</I><br>	- W. Reed Madden, "Sustainable Development Task Force" for the National Association of Counties<p>	<I>"The costs of planning in rural areas can be reduced by using the expertise of public, private, and volunteer professionals together with specialists from state universities and, increasingly, graduates of rural-planning programs."</I><br>	- From Rural Environmental Planning for Sustainable Communities by Frederic O. Sargent, et. al. <p> Small cities and towns must often look outside their own communities for informed advice on complex issues. Just as often, residents bristle when "outside experts" are consulted about local issues. Again, local participation in any sustainable effort is mandatory. "Because a rural environmental plan evolves through the direct participation of local citizens, it is more likely to be adopted and implemented," wrote Frederic O. Sargent, et. al, in Rural Environmental Planning for Sustainable Communities (Island Press).<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "75.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "77.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/76.html</h5></body></html>
