<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/77.gif"><img src="t/77.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--><I>"...underlying the whole concept of sustainable communities is the understanding that we humans are part of the larger web of natural systems, and that our continued healthy survival depends also on the healthy survival of 'living earth.'"</I><br>	- Mike Pease, "Sustainable Communities: What's Going On Here?", from Places, winter 1995<p> In places ranging from Jefferson Parish, Louisiana, to Pattonsburg, Missouri, residents and sustainability experts have teamed up to build a new future.	And, during a time of mushrooming population growth coupled with diminishing resources, a new future is what we all need.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "76.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "78.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/77.html</h5></body></html>
