<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/64.gif"><img src="t/64.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> Based in Asheville, Tennessee, HandMade in America serves 21 counties and approximately half a million people. The organization's stated goal is "to make Western North Carolina the center of handmade objects in America."The region boasts a proud history in handmade crafts, both in traditional and contemporary crafts. Members of the Cherokee Nation contribute their native crafts, including basketry and woodcarving, to the area's rich heritage. The Qualla Craft Cooperative reportedly is the nation's oldest continuing Native American cooperative.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "63.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "65.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/64.html</h5></body></html>
