<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/65.gif"><img src="t/65.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> Building on this history, HandMade in America, assisted by 360 people throughout the region, has developed a 20-year strategic plan based upon the principles of sustainable community development. The plan's goal is to establish Western North Carolina as the national center for handmade objects.Working with the North Carolina Department of Commerce and the Self Help Credit Union, HandMade in America intends to help establish a program-related investment bank which will offer low-interest loans to traditionally collateral-poor craftspeople and crafts-related businesses. And it hopes to enlist providers for health and homeowners insurance for crafters.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "64.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "66.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/65.html</h5></body></html>
