<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/58.gif"><img src="t/58.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> In 1977, the Town of Dunn initiated its Land Use Program. The program emerged in response to the "haphazard appearance of residential subdivisions and the ensuing threat to agriculture as the economic and cultural way of life in the rural township." The town enacted a two-year moratorium on subdivision development. Residents, town officials, students and educators then "worked together to develop a common land use vision for the town." The town's Land Use Plan resulted. The plan includes exclusive agricultural zoning which limits land divisions. A Land Trust has been created to permanently protect farmland and environmentally-sensitive areas.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "57.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "59.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address><h5>URL: http://<a href="http://solstice.crest.org/">solstice.crest.org</a>/<a href="/">doe</a>/<a href="/">sustainable</a>/<a href="/slideshows/">slideshows</a>/<a href="/slides/rural">rural</a>/58.html</h5></body></html>
