<TITLE>CESD: Industrial Ecology</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="/rsc/027.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<P><A HREF="/index.htm"><IMG
ALIGN="LEFT" SRC="/rsc/photow8.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<BR CLEAR="all"><BR></P>
<P>
</P>
<H1>Industrial Ecology</H1>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER><BR></P>

<H3><CENTER>CESD Industrial Ecology Recommended Reading List</CENTER></H3>


<CENTER>Allenby, B.R. and Deanna J. Richards, The Greening of Industrial Ecosystems. Washington D.C.: 	National Academy Press, 1994.</CENTER><BR>


<CENTER>Graedel, T.E. and B.R. Allenby, Industrial Ecology, Englewood Cliffs, NJ: Prentice-Hall, 1995.</CENTER><BR>


<CENTER>Hawken, Paul, The Ecology of Commerce A Declaration of Sustainability, New York: 	HarperBusiness, 1993.</CENTER><BR>


<CENTER>Socolow, R., C. Andrews, F. Berkhout, and V. Thomas, Industrial Ecology and Global Change, New 	York: Cambridge University Press, 1994.</CENTER><BR>


<CENTER>Van Der Ryn, Sim and Stuart Cowan, Ecological Design, Washington, DC: Island Press, 1996.</CENTER>

<P></P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"></CENTER>
<P><BR>  </P>
