 During such a meeting in the Willamette Valley, home to approximately 70 percent of Oregon's population, Gov. Barbara Roberts encouraged cooperative, coordinated efforts instead of independent planning. "Acting separately and independently, we will move our local urban boundaries outward over the next 20 years, likely in competition for the very same growth, sprawling, expanding, slowly covering our farmland and open space..."


