<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/74.gif"><img src="t/74.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



	<I>"...in the long term, a strong economy and a livable community cannot be sustained without a healthy environment."</I><br>

	- from "Rebuilding for the Future - A Guide to Sustainable Redevelopment for Disaster-Affected Communities" by William S. Becker, U.S. Department of Energy
<p>
 For many people worldwide, this marriage of concern for ecology with economic well-being is a familiar, if unspoken synthesis. It is familiar to small farmers who work the land and know it intimately; it is familiar also to those whose income depends upon the health of inlets, bays and seas. 


<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "73.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
