<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/21.gif"><img src="t/21.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Other evidence of Chattanooga's efforts is easy to find.  Take a look at city buses.  The city's Area Regional Transit Authority has been replacing diesel buses with new, electric shuttles manufactured in Chattanooga.

These electric buses will transport Olympic teams during the 1996 games in Atlanta. 


