<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/33.gif"><img src="t/33.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 The state of Oregon began studying global warming in 1988, when the governor's office formed an interagency task force to investigate the risks associated with warming trends.

Later, the state completed an inventory of greenhouse gases and articulated strategies for reducing related emissions to a level 20 percent below levels emitted in 1988. The state's global warming action plan considers the interaction of energy, transportation, land use, and other environmental issues.


