<!--**head**-->



 This low-income home will feature passive solar heating, a wall system of mineralized wood chips and cement, and other examples of sustainable design.
<p>
It was built in collaboration with Austin Habitat for Humanity and the American Institute of Learning. The home is part of a Green Habitat Learning Project which employs disadvantaged and "at-risk" youth to build earth-friendly homes for low-income families.



