<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/62.gif"><img src="t/62.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 During its three years of operation, the Mothers of East Los Angeles-Santa Isabel program has distributed nearly 50,000 ultra-low flush toilets (ULFTs). Other Community-Based Organizations  have also pitched in. More than 270,000 ULFTs have been distributed, resulting in an estimated savings of 3.4 billion gallons of water per year.


