<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/15.gif"><img src="t/15.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->


	<I>"Sustainability refers to the ability of a society, ecosystem, or any such ongoing system to continue functioning into the indefinite future without being forced into decline through the exhaustion...of key resources."</I><br>
	- from "Description of a Toolkit for Sustainably Redeveloping Communities" prepared for DOE by Helen J. Kessler, Sieben Associates
<p>
     Few would dispute that there is a limited supply of most of the planet's resources - clean water and air, minerals, plants, animals, agricultural land.  And residents of the United States consume a disproportionate share.
<p>
In 1992, at the U.N.-sponsored Earth Summit in Brazil, scientists spread the word. Americans, who represent only 5 per cent of the planet's population, consume one-third of the earth's resources.
<p>
Much of what we consume, we waste - through carelessness, laziness, inefficiency, and poor design.
<p>
And waste isn't just an issue of ethics. Waste hurts our health, our economy, and our quality of life. Industrial waste produces pollution. Urban waste produces abandoned downtowns and empty buildings. Energy waste produces high energy bills and oil wars...


<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "14.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
<a href = "/slideshows/urban/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a>
<a href = "16.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a>
<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
