<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/69.gif"><img src="t/69.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> From the Grassroots - Profiles of 103 Rural Self-Development Projects featured also local efforts that revitalized the downtown of Kamiah, Idaho, a small community on the Clearwater River.Beginning in 1984, in less than five years locals completed facelifts on all but two buildings along Kamiah's Main Street. Residents completed the renovations, all with a "Western Victorian" theme, without outside assistance. They held auctions, cake raffles, and other activities to raise the necessary funds. Participants included the Chamber of Commerce, retirees, schools, and civic groups such as the Lions and Kiwanis clubs.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "68.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "70.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address>

