<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/78.gif"><img src="t/78.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Francis Bacon observed that "knowledge is power." We need both knowledge and power to face the challenges of the current and coming century.
And part of what we know about sustainable development is this:<br>
1. Sustainable communities are communities with a future.<br>
2. Sustainable development is a way to consider together environmental health, economic growth, and the needs of current and future generations.<br>
3. Sustainable development is happening now, in communities across the country.<br>


