<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/44.gif"><img src="t/44.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Developed and administered by Portland's Energy Office, the Block-by-Block Weatherization Program increases energy efficiency in low-income households by providing free basic weatherization and energy-use education to eligible residents.
<p>
	As this slide shows, contractors or non-profit crews install insulation in attics, walls, or crawl spaces. To date, the program has helped weatherize 1,770 homes at a cost of about $900 per house.


