<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/52.gif"><img src="t/52.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 1000 Friends protested when planners proposed a highway bypass around Portland,  arguing such construction would only encourage additional automobile use as well as "low-density, single-use, pedestrian-hostile sprawl" along the bypass's concentric ring. The bypass also would cut across productive farmlands.


