 Another group concerned about urban sprawl is "1000 Friends of Oregon," which has been described as the nation's "leading state land use/growth management nonprofit organization." Based in Portland, 1000 Friends coordinates "Making the Land Use, Transportation, Air-Quality Connection," a national demonstration project that integrates land use, transportation, and air-quality policy.
