<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/63.gif"><img src="t/63.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Meanwhile, up the road in Santa Cruz, a much different sort of sustainable community project is under way.
<p>	
Booker T. Washington once said, "No race can prosper unless it learns that there is as much dignity in tilling a field as in writing a poem."
<p>
The Homeless Garden Project (HGP) provides jobs and meaningful work for homeless people. Workers garden in a 2.5-acre organic lot and also compost organic wastes from several local restaurants. 


<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "62.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
