<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/59.gif"><img src="t/59.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Another example of win-win sustainable development is occurring in Los Angeles. In 1992, "The Mothers of East Los Angeles-Santa Isabel" piloted a water conservation program in cooperation with city agencies and local utilities. During a period of eight weeks, one thousand ultra-low flush toilets, like these seen here in boxes, were provided free to customers of Los Angeles' Department of Water and Power.


<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "58.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
