<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/41.gif"><img src="t/41.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 The city issued itself a challenge. In five years, its energy bill would be reduced by $1 million annually, a significant savings for taxpayers. First, the Energy Office examined the city's energy bills to determine Portland's annual energy expenditures.
	Then, the Energy Office arranged energy audits. It provided technical and design assistance, arranged for energy loans, publicized projects and educated employees.
<p>
In four years, the office has identified annual savings of $950,000 in energy costs and has projects completed or under way to produce additional savings.


<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "40.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
