<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/35.gif"><img src="t/35.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Scientists know that carbon dioxide and certain other gases absorb the sun's infrared rays, warming the earth's atmosphere. Studies in Portland have determined that motor vehicles are the area's "primary CO2 villain." A 1988 study concluded that cars and trucks in the metropolitan area emitted 6.8 million metric tons of CO2.
 

<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "34.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
