<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/26.gif"><img src="t/26.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->


Chattanooga's example...<br>
<blackquote>
	"Advocates for the environment and proponents of economic development, once at odds in cities like Chattanooga, have today recognized their need for interdependence. Global pressures are forcing our businesses to be more competitive as they become more environmentally sensitive."
	<p align=right><b><i> - Mayor Gene Roberts</i></b></p>
</blockquote>
<p>
 Chattanooga's Mayor Gene Roberts is proud of his city's attempts to embrace the principles of sustainability. There has been a conscious effort to balance the needs of economic development and environmental health. As an added bonus, Chattanooga's efforts are winning national attention.
<p>
The Christian Science Monitor wrote:<br>
<I>"Today the mid-sized metropolis on the Tennessee River is earning a world-wide reputation as a model for combining environmental initiatives and economic development."</I>


<!--**foot**--><p>
