<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/47.gif"><img src="t/47.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



In another program called BEST,  "Businesses for an Environmentally Sustainable Tomorrow," Portland's Energy Office serves as a broker, helping area businesses learn about sustainable practices for their energy, water, waste, and transportation functions.
<p>
The program emphasizes energy efficiency, water conservation, waste reduction (recycling), and clean and efficient transportation. It also emphasizes and has achieved cooperation among city government agencies, utilities, state agencies, and business and professional organizations.
<p>
Meanwhile, as Portland implements innovation solutions to urban and global  problems, all Oregonians fret about Portland's growth and the associated impacts on their quality of life.
 

