<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/79.gif"><img src="t/79.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 There's still time to design a new future, one more in tune with the earth's limited resources. "Sustainability" can be the foundation for that new future.
	 A new time when degraded, polluted landscapes are historical features.  A time when the human race embraces a new relationship with ecosystems large and small, rural and urban - a relationship of sustainability.







