</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/72.gif"><img src="t/72.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 If the SRF and others succeed, Stapleton will offer "a real world example of sustainable development of significant scale." 
<p>
In Denver, in Chattanooga, and elsewhere, city planners and government officials are beginning to see that "green cities" do not exclude "greenbacks." Instead, sustainable practices can provide a profound catalyst for ailing cities. 
<p>
Vice President Al Gore emphasized this point while speaking to an audience in Chattanooga whose members included CEOs from Fortune 500 companies. Gore encouraged business leaders to consider locating in cities "deeply committed to sustainable development" which can offer "an... extraordinary quality of life for the men and women who work in the company."


<!--**foot**--><p>
