<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/67.gif"><img src="t/67.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 This is the same lot after cleaning, preparation, and conversion to a community vegetable garden.
<p>
Gardeners benefit in many ways - from improved nutrition; from savings on grocery bills; from an increased sense of self-reliance and  from the relaxing toil of horticulture. Gardens become settings for social interaction, community building, problem solving. 
<p>
Across the nation, people are working together to tackle such projects. For some, their labor is inspired by memories of a bygone era, a time of pristine swimming holes, clear skies, and fish free of mercury.
<P>
For others, a large measure of their toil is inspired by a vision of the future, a time when the young will return to play in rivers and streams, a time when our cities will no longer be shrouded in clouds of pollution.





<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "66.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
