<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Rural</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF><A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= NCSD Home Page ="></A><A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt="= Slide Shows =""></a><p><b><a href="/slides/rural/index.html">Act Locally Slide Show</a></b><br><i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p><center><a href="l/43.gif"><img src="t/43.gif"></a></center><p><!--**head**--> The silt's source was the Island Park Dam's reservoir pool. In September 1992, the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation and Idaho's Department of Fish and Game had collaborated in what turned out to be a catastrophic drawdown of the reservoir. The drawdown stirred up bottom sediments and more than 50,000 tons of silt poured into one of the country's most-celebrated trout streams. This event convinced The Henry's Fork Foundation, established in 1984, that its members must become leaders in promoting a watershed approach to protecting the river.<!--**foot**--><p><a href = "42.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a><a href = "/slides/rural/index.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/toc_button.gif" alt = "=Table of Content="></a><a href = "44.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/next_button.gif" alt = "=Next="></a><p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><address><p><a href="/rsc/comment-form.shtml">Comments &amp; Questions</a></i><b> | </b><i><a href="/rsc/suggest.shtml">Suggest a Resource</a></i></address>

