<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/34.gif"><img src="t/34.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Portland was the first major U.S. city to officially acknowledge the possibility of global warming and to take concrete steps to lessen the city's contributions to the "greenhouse effect." In March 1993, Portland hosted the "International Global Warming Solutions Symposium." In November 1993, the city announced its Carbon Dioxide Reduction Strategy.


