<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/58.gif"><img src="t/58.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->



 Austin's Green Builder Program has become a model and resource for sustainable building initiatives around the world.
	
Many "sustainable community" programs like Austin's Green Builder program provide clear-cut examples of the proverbial "win-win" situation -where the benefits reaped are economic, environmental, and human.


