<html><head><title>CESD: Slide Shows: Urban</title></head><body BGCOLOR = #FFFFFF>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/ncsdicon.gif" ALT="= CESD Home Page ="></A>
<A HREF="/slideshows/"><IMG ALIGN=middle SRC="/rsc/bugs/slides.gif" alt = "= Slide Shows ="></a>
<p>

<b><a href="/slideshows/urban/index.html">Sustainable Development Slideshow</a></b><br>
<i>National Center for Appropriate Technology</i>


<p><img SRC="/rsc/mrule.gif"><p>
<center><a href="l/10.gif"><img src="t/10.gif"></a></center>
<p>

<!--**head**-->

What is "sustainability?" What is "sustainable development?" In many ways "sustainability" is an umbrella term.

Beneath its broad cover, sustainability includes reference to innovative approaches to:<ul>
<li> energy conservation
<li> urban design
<li> waste treatment
<li> transportation
<li> urban forestry
<li> and many other disciplines.
</ul>

But what does "sustainability" really mean?


<!--**foot**--><p>
<a href = "9.html"><img src="http://solstice.crest.org/common/prev_button.gif" alt = "=Previous="></a>
