 In order to reduce carbon dioxide emissions, Portland has taken progressive measures to meet its goals. The pie chart illustrates the focus areas. Each piece represents an area targeted and notes its role in reducing carbon dioxide emissions. For example, changes made in the transportation sector are responsible for 21 percent of the total Plan's reduction goal. Most savings will come from changes made in resource utilization.

