<H2>Cover story: <A HREF="dir_zine/cover_dir/701_peninsula.html">Harsh Treatment</A></H2>
The techniques sound like they come from the dark ages of psychotherapy: straightjackets, windowless rooms, patients being "taken down" to the carpet... But these are just some of the elements of <STRONG>Peninsula Village</STRONG>'s program for deeply troubled adolescents. Do they go too far, or are they the last hope for desperate parents? <STRONG>Betty Bean</STRONG> looks at both sides of the issue.

<P ALIGN=Left><A HREF="dir_zine/ear_dir/ear.html">Ear to the Ground
</A><BR><A HREF="dir_zine/eye_dir/eye.html">Eye on the Scene
</A><BR><A HREF="dir_suncity/calendar_dir/calendar.html">The Metro Pulse
Entertainment Calendar</A>
