<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="graphics_home/search_head.gif" ALT="Dr. McDuff's Fungible Scuttlebutt Locator" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36">
<P><IMG SRC="graphics_home/engine.gif" ALIGN=LEFT ALT="(goofy Victorian-era engine)" HEIGHT=151 WIDTH=180 HSPACE="10">Looking for something? Dr. McDuff's Fungible Scuttlebutt Locator may be just the thing.
<UL><LI>Type in one or more words describing what you're looking for,
<LI>Set the Boolean operator ("AND" means all the words you enter must appear in an article, and "OR" means that at least one word must appear in an article),
<LI>Set the case sensitivity ("Insensitive" disregards the difference between upper- and lower-case letters),
<LI>and hit the "Search" button.</UL>
<P>Who knows? Maybe Dr. McDuff's marvelous contraption'll turn up something relevant.
