<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000">

<P ALIGN=Center><STRONG>January 9 - January 16, 1997</STRONG><BR>
<IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="graphics_misc/pagehead.gif" ALT="Metro Pulse Online" WIDTH="389" HEIGHT="8"><BR>
<IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="graphics_home/head_front.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36">
<P><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="graphics_home/perspex.gif" WIDTH="320" HEIGHT="232">

<H2><A HREF="dir_zine/cover_dir/701_peninsula.html">Locked Down</A></H2>
The techniques sound like they come from the dark ages of psychotherapy: straightjackets, windowless rooms, patients being "taken down" to the carpet... But these are just some of the elements of <STRONG>Peninsula Village</STRONG>'s program for deeply troubled adolescents. Do they go too far, or are they the last hope for desperate parents? <STRONG>Betty Bean</STRONG> looks at both sides of the issue.
<P>
<IMG SRC="graphics_misc/newhead.gif" ALT="NEW!" HEIGHT=52 WIDTH=72 VSPACE="3" HSPACE=5 ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="dir_suncity/movies_dir/menu.html"><STRONG>The Movie Section's online. Enjoy!</STRONG></A>
