<H3>UT FILM COMMITTEE<BR>University Center</H3>

No Films This Week

</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN="Middle" SRC="graphics_dir/hed_blurb.gif" ALT="Movie Blurbs" WIDTH="260" HEIGHT="46">

<H3><HR>101 Dalmations (G)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Jeff Daniels, Joely Richardson, Glenn Close</STRONG>
<P>Home Alone  producer John Hughes and Disney match up to create a live-action version of the classic cartoon. The fun begins when a young couple's dog gives birth to scads of too-cute-for-words puppies; the trouble arises when the evil Cruella De Vil (Close) decides their fur would make for one sharp coat.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Commons 6, East Towne Crossing 8, Foothills 8, Farragut 10

<H3><HR>The Associate (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Whoopi Goldberg, Diane Wiest, Tim Daly</STRONG>
<P>A social satire about an African-American woman who breaks through the barriers of prejudice against women in corporate industry. Laurel (Goldberg) is passed over for a well-deserved promotion, so she creates a partner, fabricating and donning the persona of "Cutty," a white, male financial whiz. Hey, if it worked for Robin Williams...
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR>Beavis &amp; Butthead (PG-13)</H3>
Yes, it's the end of western civilization as we know it--MTV's incisive pair of social critics get their own full-length animated feature. In this case, the heavy metal-loving rejects go in search of their missing TV set, traveling across America. Truly, this opens up a whole new realm of dick jokes to plunder.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10, Downtown West, Farragut 10, Foothills 8

<H3><HR>The Birds (NR)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Rod Taylor, Tippi Hedren, Jessica Tandy</STRONG>
<P>The 1963 Hitchcock classic that makes us all wince at gathering flocks of birds! 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Tennesse Theatre (double feature)

<H3><HR>The Chamber (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Gene Hackman, Chris O'Donnell</STRONG>
<P>Yet another John Grisham courtroom drama hits the big screen. This time, Gene Hackman stars as a good ol' boy racist convicted of murder and sentenced to the gas chamber; Chris O'Donnell is his grandson, who just happens to be a lawyer.
<P><STRONG>Now showing:</STRONG> Movies 7, East Towne Mall

<H3><HR>The Crucible (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Daniel Day-Lewis, Winona Ryder, Joan Allen</STRONG>
<P>The big screen adaptation of Arthur Miller's award-winning play about the Salem witch hunts. Day-Lewis plays a hardworking Puritan who dallies with the servant wench (Ryder)--first mistake. The missus catches on, Ms. Ryder gets the boot, but is persistent to a fault... The whole story is boo-scary because it was (and continues to be) based on the reality.of human imperfection. 
<P>Now Showing (Exclusively): Terrace Theatres

<H3><HR>D3-The Mighty Ducks (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Emilio Estevez</STRONG>
<P>The Mighty Ducks are now Eden Hall Warriors thanks to a hockey scholarship to an exclusive prep school-yeah! Can they take the Duck out of the Warrior? Do you care?
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR>Dear God (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Greg Kinnear, Laurie Metcalf</STRONG>
<P>Get a job or go to jail is the judge's sentence; Tom Turner (Kinnear), con artist extraordinaire, chooses a year at the U.S Post Office. Assigned to the postal purgatory known as the dead letter office, Tom devises a holiday scam of divine proportions, inspiring a frenzy of goodwill in L.A.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR><IMG SRC="graphics_dir/approved.gif" ALT="Guru Approved" HEIGHT=54 WIDTH=54 ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=5>The English Patient (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Ralph Fiennes, Juliette Binoche</STRONG>
<P>Michael Ondaatje's Booker Prize-winner novel--an elliptical collection of stories by four people who find themselves in a ruined monastery in Italy at the end of World War II--is adapted to the silver screen by director Anthony Minghella. We're talking 162 minutes of epic love stories set against the background of international upheaval.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Terrace Theatre

<H3><HR>The Evening Star (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Shirley Maclaine, Jack Nicholson</STRONG>
<P>This sequel to Terms of Endearment drops back into the life &amp; times of Aurora Greenway (Maclaine) as she grapples with teenage grandchildren and a May/December romance!
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Commons 6, Farragut 10

<H3><HR>Evita (PG)</H3>
Starts Jan. 10. Check out the Psychic Movie Preview!

<H3><HR>First Strike (PG-13)</H3>
Starts Jan. 10.  Check out the Psychic Movie Preview!

<H3><HR>The First Wives Club (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Goldie Hawn, Bette Midler, Diane Keaton</STRONG>
<P>Four high-maintenance, over-40 wives get dumped for younger trophy babes. The three survivors exact their revenge where it hurts most...in the bedrooms and boardrooms of their respective ex's. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR>Fly Away Home (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Anna Pacquin, Jeff Daniels, Dana Delaney</STRONG>
<P>The poignant tale of a 13-year-old girl struggling with losing her mother and becoming reacquainted with her estranged father. Their relationship grows after she hatches a nest of orphaned Canadian goose eggs and together they focus on teaching them to migrate south. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Movies 7

<H3><HR>Ghosts of Mississippi (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Whoopi Goldberg, James Woods, Alec Baldwin</STRONG>
<P>The drama surrounding the third trial of Byron de la Beckwith, charged with the 1963 murder of civil rights leader Medgar Evers.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10, Downtown West, Farragut 10, 

<H3><HR>Jerry MaGuire (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Tom Cruise, Cuba Gooding Jr., Kelly Preston, and Bonnie Hunt </STRONG>
<P>Cruise is a high-powered sports agent who suddenly loses his job, his girlfriend, and his shallow pals. He manages to convince one co-worker (she's cute! she's blonde!) and one client (a skeptical black athlete) to follow him as he forms his own independent agency.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Commons 6, Foothills 8, East Towne Crossing 8, Farragut 10, Halls Cinema 7. 

<H3><HR>Jingle All the Way (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Arnold Schwarznegger, Rita Wilson, Phil Hartman, Sinbad</STRONG>
<P>Arnold's kid wants the hottest action figure of the season, while supply falls painfully short of demand. As a result, many eager parents elbow and punch their way to the check-out aisles. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR>The Long Kiss Goodnight (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Geena Davis, Samuel L. Jackson</STRONG>
<P>Jackson plays a detective who helps a polite, unassuming P.T.A. mom (Davis), afflicted with amnesia. As her past slowly resurfaces, it becomes obvious he's hanging with a government trained hit-person being hotly pursued by the same. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR>The Man Who Knew Too Much (NR)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Jimmy Stewart, Doris Day </STRONG>
<P>The 1956 Hitchcock classic (actually a remake of his own 1934 film) follows Stewart and Day as they trek from Marrakech to the U.K. looking for their kidnapped son. Amid the hubub, Day somehow finds time to sing "Que Sera Sera." 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Tennese Theatre (double feature)

<H3><HR><IMG SRC="graphics_dir/approved.gif" ALT="Guru Approved" HEIGHT=54 WIDTH=54 ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=5>Mars Attacks (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Jack Nicholson(in two roles), Glenn Close, and a cast of thousands</STRONG>
<P>Nicholson plays smarmy President Dale to Close's vapid First Lady Dale as aliens attack Washington. Sound familiar? This adaptation of a bubble gum trading card series is part-spoof and part-tribute to tacky '50s monster movies, chi-chi '60s sci-fi thrillers, and corny '70s disaster flicks. The martians rock.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10

<H3><HR>Michael (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: John Travolta, John Hurt, Andie McDowell, John Pastorelli, Gene Stapleton</STRONG>
<P>The Archangel Michael comes to call in a small Iowa town. The unkempt, lusty emissary of God smites a bank for the widow who prays him to earth and stays to play matchmaker to the National Enquirer wannabes who respond to get the scoop. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10, Downtown West, Farragut 10, Halls Cinema 7

<H3><HR>My Fellow Americans (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Jack Lemmon, James Garner, Dan Aykroyd</STRONG>
<P>Another on-the-road buddy comedy with a twist--in this case, the odd couple are a pair of ex-Presidents. Lemmon and Garner co-star as the two former leaders of the free world, one liberal and one conservative, who must join forces when the current Nixon-esque prez (Aykroyd) frames them.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Commons 6, East Towne Crossing 8, Farragut 10

<H3><HR>One Fine Day (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Michelle Pfeiffer, George Clooney</STRONG>
<P>Pfeiffer plays a hot single mom who accidentally swaps cell phones with Clooney, a hot single dad and ace reporter. After many cellular conversations, sparks fly amid the microwaves. Let the romance commence.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Downtown West, Farragut 10, Foothills 8, Halls Cinema 7

<H3><HR>The People vs. Larry Flynt (R)</H3>
Starts Jan. 10. Check out the Psychic Movie Preview!

<H3><HR>The Preacher's Wife (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Denzel Washington, Whitney Houston, Courtney B. Vance</STRONG>
<P>Director Penny "Laverne" Marshall (Big) remakes the 1947 comedy The Bishop's Wife, wherein an angel comes to the aid of a troubled ministry. In this case, Denzel Washington is the angel, and the preacher's wife is Whitney Houston.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10, Farragut 10, Foothills 8, Downtown West

<H3><HR>Ransom (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Mel Gibson, Rene Russo, Gary Sinise</STRONG>
<P>Tom Mullen (Gibson) is a corporate magnate who has it all: money, a Barbie wife, a cute kid, fame. A sudden downside occurs when the child becomes the target of a kidnapping. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10, Downtown West

<H3><HR>The Relic (R)</H3>
Opening Jan 10. Check out the Psychic Movie Preview!

<H3><HR><IMG SRC="graphics_dir/approved.gif" ALT="Guru Approved" HEIGHT=54 WIDTH=54 ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=5>Romeo &amp; Juliet (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Leonardo DiCaprio, Claire Danes</STRONG>
<P>The rock 'n' roll version of Shakespeare's classic tale of star-crossed young love finds a hip group of heartsick teens living and dying in "South Florida," minus the affected English accents and tights.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Downtown West, East Towne Mall, Movies 7

<H3><HR>Scream (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Courtney Cox, Drew Barymore</STRONG>
<P>Schlock master Wes Craven (The Hills Have Eyes, A Nightmare on Elm Street) sends up his own genre with this comedy-horror film that encapsulates as many clichs as possible. High school students Barrymore and Campbell are stalked by a (you guessed it!) psycho-killer. Cox appears as a reporter. 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Cinema 10, Downtown West, Farragut 10, Halls Cinema 7, 

<H3><HR>Sleepers (R)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Brad Pitt, Jason Patric, Robert DeNiro, Kevin Bacon</STRONG>
<P>The first half of this purported true story centers on a pack of pubescent boys in Hell's Kitchen in the 1960s and the hellish mistreatment they suffer in a juvenile facility; the second half flashes forward 15 years and finds the boys--now all grown-up--seeking both recklessly impulsive and cleverly plotted revenge.
<P><STRONG>Now showing:</STRONG> East Towne Mall

<H3><HR>Small Wonder (G)</H3>
Starts Jan. 10. Check out the Psychic Movie Preview!

<H3><HR>Space Jam (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Michael Jordan, Bugs Bunny</STRONG>
<P>An evil intergalactic amusement park owner kidnaps the Looney Tunes and some of the NBA's finest. Bugs challenges the evildoers to a full-court duel to determine their fate, recruiting Jordan for the home team.
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> East Towne Crossing 8

<H3><HR><IMG SRC="graphics_dir/approved.gif" ALT="Guru Approved" HEIGHT=54 WIDTH=54 ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=5>Star Trek: First Contact (PG-13)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Patrick Stewart, Brent Spiner, Michael Dorn, Jonathan Frakes</STRONG>
<P>The eighth Trek movie delivers a new Enterprise (leaner and meaner!), and a lot more action and special effects. Without any of the original '60s <STRONG>cast left, the "Next Generation" at last has a mission of its own: kick Borg butt.</STRONG>
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG> Commons 6, East Towne Crossing 8

<H3><HR>That Thing You Do! (PG)</H3>
<STRONG>Cast: Tom Hanks, Tom Everett, Kevin Pollack, Peter Scolari, Johnathon Schaech</STRONG>
<P>The Wonders--a rag tag Pennsylvania garage band--get their 15 minutes of fame after a radio hit propels them to star status (and a free-fall into oblivion). 
<P><STRONG>Now Showing:</STRONG>  Movies 7

<H3><HR>Turbulence (R)</H3>
Starts Jan. 10. Check out the Psychic Movie Preview!

