<H2><HR><A NAME="saturday">Saturday, January 11</A></H2>
<P><STRONG>BR5-49 W/CHARLIE MAJOR</STRONG> Sure, insurgent country or alterna-country or twangcore or whatever you wanna call it is trendy as heck, in all its Gram Parsons--(or, God forbid, the Eagles--) inspired glory. But BR5-49 (the name is nicked from a Hee-Haw skit) don't go that route, leaving it to the sweethearts of the rodeo while they conjure up the hotfoot spirits of Hank Sr., Bob Wills, and Marty Robbins--country music as vintage as the Kentucky Colonel string ties they wear onstage every night. Although they've been accused of camp (perhaps it's the matching suits and hats), it seems to be BR5-49 take their country tributes and send-ups to heart, albeit with a sly grin. At: Flamingo's, 9pm. $7
<P><STRONG>J.D. CROWE &AMP; THE NEW SOUTH W/IIIRD TYME OUT</STRONG> <A HREF="spotlights.html">See Spotlight</A>. At: Bijou Theatre, 7:30pm. $15. (656-4444)
<P><STRONG>J.D. CROWE &AMP; THE NEW SOUTH</STRONG> At: Disc Exchange South, 3pm. FREE
<P><STRONG>BR5-49</STRONG> At: Disc Exchange South, 5pm. FREE
<P><STRONG>1964: THE TRIBUTE</STRONG> <A HREF="spotlights.html">See Spotlight</A>. At: Tennesee Theatre, 8pm. $15. (656-4444)
<P><STRONG>TRIPTONIC W/BOBFOSSIL</STRONG> Technodelic ambience. At: Gryphon's, 9pm. FREE
<P><STRONG>TENNESSEE KINGSNAKES W/ #1 FAMILY MOVER AND HAZEL VIRTUE</STRONG> At: Mercury Theatre, 10pm.
<P><STRONG>ARMCHAIR BUDDHA</STRONG> At: Manhattan's, 10pm. FREE
<P><STRONG>HAMBONE PIE</STRONG> At: Sassy Ann's, 9:30pm. $3
<P><STRONG>VALENTINE</STRONG> At: The Spot, 10pm.
<P><STRONG>JIMI AND JOHN</STRONG> At: The Mill, 10pm.
<P><STRONG>TBA</STRONG> At: The Frog, 9:30pm.
<P><STRONG>RICHARD GILEWITZ</STRONG> At: Ossoli Auditorium, 8pm.
<P><STRONG>DAVE KING TRIO</STRONG> At: Mattioda's, 9pm.
