<H2><HR><A NAME="opencall">Open Call</A></H2>

<H3>Volunteers</H3>
<P><STRONG>GOODWILL INDUSTRIES</STRONG> needs volunteers to assist with the fifth annual Super Book Sale, to be held at Oak Ridge Mall Fri.-Sun., Jan. 10-12. Call 588-8567.
<P><STRONG>HUMAN-ANIMAL BOND IN TENNESSEE (HABIT)</STRONG> will hold a volunteer interest meeting on Sat., Jan. 11, 10am, at the University of Tennessee Veterinary Teaching Hospital, room 118. The animal-assisted therapy program conducts therapeutic visits to nursing homes, rehab centers, schools, and other facilities. Call 974-5633.

<H3>Theater/Film</H3>
<P><STRONG>CUMBERLAND COUNTY PLAYHOUSE</STRONG> will hold auditions for upcoming productions on Sat., Jan. 18, at the theater in Crossville. Teens and adult volunteers may audition from 1-2pm, and kids ages 8-12 are welcome from 2-3pm. No experience or prepared material is necessary. Professionals, interns, and advanced volunteers may audition by appointment from 3-6pm. Call 484-4324, ext. 243. Shows include Anne of Green Gables, Smoke On The Mountain, and The Music Man.
<P><STRONG>THE BIJOU THEATRE</STRONG> will hold auditions for The Miracle Worker on Sat., Jan. 18 and Sun., Jan. 19, 2-4pm, at the theater. Auditions will consist of readings from the script; roles are available for four males and 12 females, ages 8-60. Call 523-4211.
<P><STRONG>THE OAK RIDGE JUNIOR PLAYHOUSE</STRONG> will hold auditions for Hallelujah Hopscotch on Sat. and Sun., Jan. 18 and 19, 1pm, at the playhouse. Roles are available for kids and teen; volunteers are needed. Auditions will consist of dance and movement, improvisation, and readings from the script. Call 482-9999.
<P><STRONG>FILM AUDITIONS</STRONG> for a Knoxville production will be held Sun. and Mon., Jan. 19 and 20. Roles are available for one female between the ages of 20 and 30, and three males ages 21-35. Call 675-6523 for an appointment.
<P><STRONG>THE CLARENCE BROWN THEATRE</STRONG> will hold open auditions for Andorra on Fri., Jan. 31, 7-11pm; and Sat., Feb. 1, 1-6pm, at the Ula Love Doughty Carousel Theatre. Roles are available for males and females of various ages. Auditionees should bring a prepared piece no more than two minutes in length. To schedule an appointment, call 974-0964.

<H2><HR><A NAME="openbook">Open Book</A></H2>
<P><STRONG>INVESTMENT ADVISERS DON NALLS AND BRAD BOWER</STRONG> will discuss investment strategies on Fri., Jan. 10, 10:30am, at Davis-Kidd Booksellers.
<P><STRONG>KAREN DAVIS</STRONG> presents her 1997 Travel Slide Presentation at Davis-Kidd Booksellers on Sun., Jan. 12, 6:30pm. Preview upcoming trips to Ireland, Wales, and Mexico; for info on the trips or the presentation, call 690-0136.
<P><STRONG>LISA ROSS, C.N.M., AND LINDA COLE, C.N.M.,</STRONG> will discuss "Midwifery--Explore Options in Pregnancy and Childbirth" on Thurs., Jan. 16, 6:30pm, at Davis-Kidd Booksellers.
<P><STRONG>TRACY JONES</STRONG> (a.k.a. romance novelist Tracy South) signs copies of The Fiance Thief on Sat., Jan. 18, 4-6pm, at Bookstar.
<P><STRONG>JACK NEELY</STRONG> is the guest lecturer at Blount Mansion on Sun., Jan. 19, 2pm; the topic of discussion is "Knoxville's Presidential Candidate: Hugh Lawson White."
<P><STRONG>TWIGTALK,</STRONG> Knoxville's newest poetry/spoken word open mike, happens every Sunday night, 9pm, upstairs at the Longbranch Saloon. Hosted by local freak Rus Harper, TwigTalk is uncensored, noncompetitive, and free.
<P><STRONG>PURELY POETRY,</STRONG> a monthly poetry reading, will be held at Bookstar the first Thursday of each month, 7pm. To sign up, call 584-1006.
<P><STRONG>STEP UP TO THE OPEN MIKE</STRONG> at Joe Muggs (Books-A-Million) the first Tuesday of each month, beginning at 8pm.
