<P>
<A NAME=American><IMG SRC="rg_heds/american.gif" ALT="AMERICAN" WIDTH="192" HEIGHT="64"></A>
<P><STRONG>Applebee's
</STRONG><BR>6928 Kingston Pike, 588-0766
<BR>261 N. Peters Rd., 531-5819
<BR>3216 Mall Road Circle, 523-2600
<BR>5316 Central Ave. Pike, 689-3300
<BR>Standard American fare served in a convivial gathering-place atmosphere.
Menu includes some tasty, vegetarian-friendly dishes. Sun.-Sat. 11am-2am.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Applewood's
</STRONG><BR>West Knoxville, 996-1160
<BR>Americana, country cuisine for breakfast, lunch or dinner. Highlights
include specialty salads, steaks and ribs. Breakfast with all the fixings.
Although they don't open until mid-October, plans include lake views and
a landscaped boardwalk. Group and banquet facilities available. Hours not
yet set, but they'll be open year round.
<P><STRONG>The Bistro
<BR></STRONG>807 S. Gay, 544-0537
<BR>For lunch or dinner, an escape for the downtown professional and/or Bijou
concert-goer, with fresh fish brought in daily and a variety of outstanding
pasta dishes. Weekday happy hour is from 4-7pm and features 99-cent draft
beer and ten-cent wings, and they're open before and after all Bijou events
(excluding Sunday matinees). Mon.-Fri. 11am-9pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Bob Evans
<BR></STRONG>211 N. Cedar Bluff, 690-3739
<BR>5604 Merchants Blvd., 689-8555
<BR>Breakfast all day and traditional home-style staples, with special menus
for seniors and children, and weekday breakfast and lunch specials. Sun.-Thurs.
6am-10pm, Fri.-Sat. 6am-11:30pm, MC/V, No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Bullfeathers
<BR></STRONG>10535 Kingston Pike, 690-1786
<BR>Beef (that's the bull) and chicken (that's the feathers). Try their homemade
chicken cordon bleu or baby back ribs. Karaoke Thurs. &amp; Fri.; live
entertainment Sat. night. Lunch Tues.-Fri. 11am-3pm, dinner Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm, closed Sun. Lunch under $5, dinner $7-$12.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer and wine coolers; bring the rest if you like.
<P><STRONG>Charlie Peppers
<BR></STRONG>716 20th Street, 524-8669
<BR>Nope. It ain't Mexican. They feature mild to wild cuisine--from their
spicy Southwestern salads to the soon-to-be-famous Jackelope sandwich. Also
featuring great burgers and chicken. Open daily 11am-midnight. All items
under $12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Darryl's
<BR></STRONG>6604 Kingston Pike, 584-1879
<BR>5616 Merchants Ctr. Blvd., 688-1792
<BR>Barbecue (a specialty) and more. The most succulent fried mushrooms
imaginable. Zany atmosphere--where else in town can you eat in an elevator?
Mon.-Thurs. 11am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight, Sun 10am-midnight.
$7 - $12. V/MC/AE/DC/ CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Grady's Goodtimes
<BR></STRONG>6741 Kingston Pike, 584-4663
<BR>318 N. Peters Rd., 694-4663
<BR>High-quality, heart-smart American fare in an intimate, relaxing atmosphere.
This Knoxville original has recently returned to its original menu. Be sure
not to miss their famous (infamous?) chocolate bar cake. Yum! Sun.-Thurs.
11am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine,
liquor.
<P><STRONG>Hanna's Cafe
<BR></STRONG>1901 Cumberland Ave., 522-9933
<BR>With paint-by-number mountain scenes as the main decor, how can you go
wrong? Calzones, salads and one of the best burgers around. Check out the
selection of gourmet coffees. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. 12pm-1am. Delivery until midnight. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine,
liquor.
<P><STRONG>Hawkeye's
<BR></STRONG>1717 White Ave., 524-5326
<BR>An old campus favorite with an extensive, affordable menu plus free local
entertainment and daily drink specials. Once again our readers gave them
a "Best Happy Hour" in our Best of Knoxville poll. The wings are only one
of the appetizers to pick from. Sunday brunch on the porch. Like visiting
your friend's house for dinner. $7-$12 Mon.-Sat. 11am-2am, Sun. 11am-2am.
V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Ivory's
<BR></STRONG>4705 Old Kingston Pike, 588-6023
<BR>A "nice quiet piano lounge" with weekly jazz including appearances by
Spencer Cordon and the David Binkley Duo. Entertainment starts at 8pm Wed.
&amp; Thurs.; Fri.-Sat. the music starts at 9pm. Prime rib and dinner specials.
Mon., Wed. &amp; Thurs. 11am-10pm., Tues. 11am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. 3pm-midnight. Lunch under $7, dinner $7-$12. MC/V/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Manhattan's
<BR></STRONG>101 S. Central Ave., 525-4463
<BR>Regular menu favorites include Philly cheese steak, fish and chips, and
a good selection of vegetarian items. Feast on the specialty of the house,
the Old City Reuben: corned beef, turkey, Swiss cheese, sauerkraut, Russian
dressing and Dijon mustard on grilled pumpernickel. Now open for Sunday champagne
brunch. Mon.-Sun. 11am-3pm , Tues &amp; Thurs. 11am-12am, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-3am. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>McGuffey's
<BR></STRONG>100 N. Seven Oaks Dr., , 691-8914
<BR>Windsor Sq.
<BR>A light, healthy menu is now available, but their HUGE cheese sticks
are
an absolute must. Try the blackened Cajun specialties. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-11pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-12pm. Lunch under $7, Dinner $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Miami Subs Grill
<BR></STRONG>9739 Kingston Pike, 691-1266
<BR>The timing of fast food with the feel of a full-service restaurant. Chow
down on a cheese steak sub or gyro, and top it off with some frozen yogurt.
But remember: the indoor playground is for kids only. Sun-Thurs. 10:30am-12am,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 10:30am-1am. Under $7. V/MC/AE. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>The Mill
<BR></STRONG>Western Plaza, 588-0080
<BR>Brewery, bakery, restaurant...what else could you want? The muffins are
good--the guilt-free chocolate is a low-fat indulgence. The food is great--try
the fabulous wild mushroom meatloaf or the grilled pork loin in Jack Daniel's
mustard cream sauce. But the real standout is the beer--have the harvest
gold, the magic brew, the Rocky Top red, or the studly stout. Liquid refreshment
at its best. Mon.-Wed. 11am-11pm, Thurs.-Sun. 11am-1am. $7-$15. V/MC/AE.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Mountain Harbor Inn
<BR></STRONG>1199 Hwy. 139, Dandridge, 397-3345
<BR>This delightful inn specializes in prime rib, steaks, pasta, and char-grilled
seafood and chicken. A variety of breads and desserts all made in house.
Chef Jock Ligoi from the Tastebuds Cafe will be the guest chef this summer.
Dining room closed Jan.-March (except for private parties). Tues.-Fri.
11:30am-2:30pm, 5:30pm-9pm, Sat. 11:30am-9pm, Sun. 12am-3pm. Lunch $3.95-$9.95,
dinner $12-$18. V/MC/D/AE. BYOB.
<P><STRONG>O'Charley's
<BR></STRONG>1915 Cumberland Ave., 525-7665
<BR>8029 Kingston Pike, 693-2322
<BR>117 Cedar Lane , 689-2870
<BR>Yummy after-hours appetizers and late-night late patio fun. Good salads
and sandwiches for lunch. Try their roast beef or fresh seafood specials
for dinner. Special lunch deals for the cost-conscious. Mon.-Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. 11am-10pm. Lunch under $7, dinner $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Old College Inn
<BR></STRONG>2204 Cumberland Ave., 523-4597
<BR>Enjoy A+ burgers, ribeye sandwiches, grilled chicken specialties, and
much more in the lowest of low-key atmospheres. A campus institution and
night owl sanctuary. Mon.-Sat. 11am-2:30am, Sun. 12pm-2:30am. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Patrick Sullivan's
<BR></STRONG>100 N. Central, 522-4511
<BR>7545 Northshore Dr., 694-9696
<BR>Meals of the Irish pub variety. Blue-plate specials feature homemade
mashed
potatoes and fresh veggies. Wonderful turn-of-the-century saloon atmosphere
in the Old City. Old City hours Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-midnight. West location hours closes at 11pm Fri. &amp; Sat. Both locations
closed Sunday. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Rafferty's Restaurant &amp; Bar
<BR></STRONG>8906 Kingston Pike , 539-1323
<BR>Self-dubbed "The American Grille," Rafferty's cooks its American fare
over an open hickory wood fire. And, refreshingly, all its salads are made
fresh to order. The atmosphere is upbeat, with an abundance of plants and
a soundtrack featuring the ever-popular hits of the '50s, '60s, and '70s.
Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $6-$17. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>R.J.'S Courtyard
<BR></STRONG>3749 Airport Hwy., 970-7777
<BR>Tempting American cuisine in a relaxed tropical setting for the plane-weary
traveler. Try the garden burger or their dessert specialty: an ice cream
Idaho baked potato(?!). Sun.-Thurs. 11am-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10:30pm.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine coolers.
<P><STRONG>Ruby Tuesday's
<BR></STRONG>East Towne Mall, 524-1237
<BR>West Town Mall, 690-3737
<BR>All-American menu featuring beef and chicken dishes, plus homemade soups
and an extensive salad bar. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Soup Kitchen
<BR></STRONG>9246 Park West Blvd., 539-6500
<BR>This West Knoxville offshoot of one of downtown's favorite lunch spots
offers the same array of fine soups (voted "Best" in our Reader's Poll),
and dinner to boot. Mon.-Fri. 11am-8pm, Sat. &amp; Sun. 11am-2pm. Under $7.
<P><STRONG>Sunspot
<BR></STRONG>1909 Cumberland Ave., 524-3380
<BR>The Sunspot offers top-notch seafood, pasta, sandwiches and steaks for
lunch and dinner, and a wide variety of "Best of Knoxville" vegetarian dishes.
The warm, inviting, urbane atmosphere is a welcome escape from the hustle
and bustle of UT's "strip." $7-$12. Mon.-Sat. 11am-11pm, closed Sundays.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>T.G.I. Friday's
<BR></STRONG>1613 Downtown West Blvd., 690-3273
<BR>All the classics (burgers, fries) plus a few wonderfully unexpected surprises
like the baked brie with pesto and roasted garlic. For the light eater, they
offer a wide variety of salads and light items. They claim their happy hour
is the best in town, and won "Best Appetizers" in our '96 Reader's Poll.
Happy Hour Mon.-Fri. 4pm-7pm, $1 drafts, and $1 off all mixed drinks. Sun.-Thurs.
11am-12am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><A NAME=BBQ><IMG SRC="rg_heds/bbq.gif" ALT="BBQ" WIDTH="139" HEIGHT="55"></A>
<P><STRONG>Calhoun's
<BR></STRONG>400 Neyland Dr., 673-3355
<BR>       10020 Kingston Pike , 673-3444
<BR>       While you're enjoying the delicious barbecued ribs that were voted
"Best
Ribs" in Knoxville in our '96 Readers Poll (for the second year in a row),
take in the fabulous river front view (or lakefront view, or, well, interstate
view). Don't miss such instant Knoxville classics as spinach Maria, white
bean chili, and the original onion loaf. Mon.-Fri. 11am-10pm, Sat.-Sun.
11am-11pm. $7-$17. V/MC/AE/DC/D/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Calhoun's BBQ &amp; Brew
<BR></STRONG>6515 Kingston Pike, 673-3377
<BR>       This youngest branch of the Calhoun family tree has all that you've
come
to expect from its cousins: consistently good sandwiches, grilled chicken
and steaks, ribs and pork, and salads. But with the addition of an in-house
brewery, the specialty of this house is the handcrafted brew. Another Thunder
Road, anyone? Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight, Sun.
11am-9pm. $7-$12. V/ MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Corky's Ribs &amp; B.B.Q.
<BR></STRONG>260 North Peters Rd., 690-3137
<BR>       Ribs, ribs, and more ribs. Be sure to try them both wet and dry.
Memphis
made this place an institution, so no wonder their famous B.B.Q. pork and
B.B.Q. sauce was voted #1 in Knoxville in our Reader's Poll. Also, drop by
for happy hour: Mon.-Fri. from 3pm to 8pm and all day Sat. &amp; Sun. Sun.-Thurs.
11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$14. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Sarge's BBQ
<BR></STRONG>3506 Pleasant Ridge Rd., 544-1440
<BR>       Home-grown barbecue that has more than earned its devoted cult
following.
Don't leave without trying the authentic Virgin Island style ginger cakes.
Mon.-Wed. 10am-10pm, Thurs.-Sat. 10am-midnight. Closed Sunday. Under $7.
No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Scruggs Real Pit Barbeque &amp; Package Store
<BR></STRONG>1920 Magnolia Ave., 524-4333
<BR>       What more do you need? Real deal 'que, and--if you get it to go--your
choice of beer, wine or liquor from their full-service package store. Mon.-Thurs.
10am-9pm, Fri.-Sat. 10am-midnight, open varying hours Sundays. Under $7-$12.
No credit cards. Beer, wine, liquor for off-premises consumption only.
<P><STRONG>Tic-Toc
<BR></STRONG>3240 E. Magnolia Ave., 522-6901
<BR>       An East Knoxville barbecue icon of the "dry" variety. Mon.-Sat.
10am-10pm.
Under $7. No credit cards. Beer only.
<P><A NAME=Burgers><IMG SRC="rg_heds/burgers.gif" ALT="BURGERS" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="69"></A>
<P><STRONG>Bel Air Grill
<BR></STRONG>9117 Executive Park Dr.	694-0606
<BR>       3802 Neal Dr. (in Halls)	922-5522
<BR>       2650 Airport Hwy. (in Alcoa)	981-3788
<BR>       Burgers, shakes, fries and other authentic throw-back '50s fare.
If '90s
fare is more your style, try the steaks and chicken. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12+. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine coolers.
<P><STRONG>Hooray's
<BR></STRONG>106 S. Central		546-6729
<BR>       Cavernous sports bar with excellent soups, salads and traditional
meat-and-potatoes fare--voted the "Best Sports Bar" in Knoxville in our reader's
poll twice running, for all the right reasons. Wear orange. Mon.-Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. Noon-3am. Under $12. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Litton's
<BR></STRONG>2803 Essary Dr.		688-0429
<BR>       Burgers worth waiting in line for--they were voted "Best Burger"
in town
in our '96 Readers Poll. Supporting roles played by the incredible blue-plate
lunches and delicious homemade desserts have made Litton's a Knoxville
institution. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm. $7-12. Cash
and local checks. BYOB.
<P><STRONG>Rally's Hamburgers
<BR></STRONG>2320 Chapman Hwy.	573-8567
<BR>       The fastest, the cheapest, and some of the tastiest burgers among
the
fast-food joints. Mon.-Sun. 10am-11pm. Way under $7. No credit cards. No
alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Sassy Ann's
<BR></STRONG>820 N. Fourth Ave.	525-5839
<BR>       Situated in an old Victorian home, this Fourth &amp; Gill neighborhood
restaurant and pub has got to be the comfiest spot in town in which to belly
up to the bar. Relax on the new patio and enjoy cool outdoor drink specials.
Also, their burgers are HUGE. Tues.-Sun. (deck and downstairs) 3pm-3am, upstairs
bar opens at 7pm. Closed Mondays. V/MC/AE/D. Beer.
<P><A NAME=Cafe><IMG SRC="rg_heds/cafe.gif" ALT="CAFE" WIDTH="144" HEIGHT="75"></A>
<P><STRONG>Amsterdam Cafe
<BR></STRONG>102 Central St. , 523-2437
<BR>       A comfortable cafe/pub in the heart of the Old City with high
tables and
hardwood floors. Try the gourmet pizzas, turkey wraps, or the black bean
and veggie quesidillas. With over 100 different bottled beers to choose from,
and twenty on tap, it's no wonder it's been dubbed the "Best Beer Selection"
in town by our readers. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-?, Fri &amp; Sat. 11am-3am, Sun.
6pm-12am. Under $7. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Aubrey's Courthouse Cafe
