<P><STRONG>Tjaarda's
<BR></STRONG>118 S. Central Ave., 637-8702
<BR>    Veteran Knoxville chef Mike Tjaarda creates vegetarian and seafood
specialties
to fill what was once a glaring void in the local restaurant scene. Try the
black bean and spinach lasagna, crab cakes, or pierogies with a bottle from
their inexpensive wine list. Lunch: Mon.-Fri. 11am-2pm, Dinner: Mon.-Thurs.
5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer and wine.
<P><A NAME=Vietnamese><IMG SRC="rg_heds/vietnamese.gif" ALT="VIETNAMESE" WIDTH="206" HEIGHT="61"></A>
<P><STRONG>T. Ho
<BR></STRONG>815 Merchants Dr., 688-5815
<BR>    Vietnamese specialties and incredible spring rolls. Try the eggless
crepe
with shrimp. Tues.-Fri. 11am-9:30pm, Sat. 5pm-10pm, Sun. Noon-9pm. Under
$7. V/MC/AE. BYOB.
<P><A NAME=Wings><IMG SRC="rg_heds/wings.gif" ALT="WINGS & THINGS" WIDTH="114" HEIGHT="104"></A>
<P><STRONG>bw3
<BR></STRONG>109 N. Central Ave., 522-4293
<BR>    In case you haven't guessed from the initials, Buffalo-style chicken
wings
are the specialty of the house. They also offer salads, grilled items from
"Southwest of the border," and Knoxville's largest selection of draft beers.
Voted "Best Wings" by our readers one more time. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-2:30am,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Hooter's
<BR></STRONG>8050 Kingston Pike, 694-4668
<BR>    Finger foods for the sports fanatic: wings, oysters, clams, crab
legs
and shrimp. Their wait staff is tops (wink, wink, nudge, nudge). Mon.-Thurs.
11am-12pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-1am, Sun. 1pm-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE. Beer
only.
<P><STRONG>Spicy's
<BR></STRONG>1800 Cumberland Ave., 523-4723
<BR>    Buffalo wings and cold beer: a match made in heaven. Mon.-Wed. 11am-1am,
Thurs. &amp; Sat. 11am-1:30am, Sun. 11am-11pm. (Summer hours may vary.) Under
$7. V/MC/D. Beer only.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
