<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_campus.gif" ALT="Campus Area" WIDTH="131" HEIGHT="32">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>Charlie Peppers
<BR></STRONG>716 20th Street, 524-8669
<BR>Nope. It ain't Mexican. They feature mild to wild cuisine--from their
spicy Southwestern salads to the soon-to-be-famous Jackelope sandwich. Also
featuring great burgers and chicken. Open daily 11am-midnight. All items
under $12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Hanna's Cafe
<BR></STRONG>1901 Cumberland Ave., 522-9933
<BR>With paint-by-number mountain scenes as the main decor, how can you go
wrong? Calzones, salads and one of the best burgers around. Check out the
selection of gourmet coffees. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. 12pm-1am. Delivery until midnight. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine,
liquor.
<P><STRONG>Hawkeye's
<BR></STRONG>1717 White Ave., 524-5326
<BR>An old campus favorite with an extensive, affordable menu plus free local
entertainment and daily drink specials. Once again our readers gave them
a "Best Happy Hour" in our Best of Knoxville poll. The wings are only one
of the appetizers to pick from. Sunday brunch on the porch. Like visiting
your friend's house for dinner. $7-$12 Mon.-Sat. 11am-2am, Sun. 11am-2am.
V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Old College Inn
<BR></STRONG>2204 Cumberland Ave., 523-4597
<BR>Enjoy A+ burgers, ribeye sandwiches, grilled chicken specialties, and
much more in the lowest of low-key atmospheres. A campus institution and
night owl sanctuary. Mon.-Sat. 11am-2:30am, Sun. 12pm-2:30am. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Sunspot
<BR></STRONG>1909 Cumberland Ave., 524-3380
<BR>The Sunspot offers top-notch seafood, pasta, sandwiches and steaks for
lunch and dinner, and a wide variety of "Best of Knoxville" vegetarian dishes.
The warm, inviting, urbane atmosphere is a welcome escape from the hustle
and bustle of UT's "strip." $7-$12. Mon.-Sat. 11am-11pm, closed Sundays.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Cafe
</H2><P><STRONG>The Torch
<BR></STRONG>1701 Cumberland Ave., 525-7713
<BR>       Gyros and Greek specialties, vegetarian sandwiches, soups and
assorted
short-order fare. Catch their Saturday night coffeehouse-style poetry reading.
Mon.-Fri. 8am-8pm, Sat. 8:30am-1am, Sun. 9am-3:30pm. Under $7. No credit
cards. No alcohol.
<H2>Coffee Shop
</H2><P><STRONG>11th Street Expresso House
<BR></STRONG>Corner of Clinch &amp; 11th St., 546-3003
<BR> Who'd've thunk it--a coffeehouse in an actual house. The front porch
and
back patio surrounded by trees make for instant atmosphere, and inside it's
cozy as can be. There's no smoking, so treat yourself to Nancy's special
hot cocoa and a big muffin instead. Mon.-Fri. 4pm until 1am, Sat. &amp; Sun.
12pm-2am. Under $7. Cash only. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Cup-A-Joe
<BR></STRONG>1911 Cumberland Ave. , 673-3148
<BR>It's not just a coffee shop anymore. This hangout offers a full line
of
desserts, imported hand rolled cigars, and literary magazines. It's smoker
friendly, but high ceilings and ceiling fans keep the air on the move. Live
music Friday nights. Mon.-Sun. 8am-2am. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D, checks accepted.
No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Daily Grind
<BR></STRONG>1823 Cumberland Ave, 971-5406
<BR>A relaxed yet energetic espresso house perfect for a good game of chess,
or checkers--or relaxing on one of the many futons. Homemade baked goods
available. Try the Fudge Brownie Delight, tell 'em to add the raspberry truffle.
Mon.-Thurs. 11am-12am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-1am, Sun. 1pm-12am. Under $7.
cash only.
<P><STRONG>The Varsity Inn
<BR></STRONG>1713 Cumberland Ave., 523-8903
<BR>    The place to go for breakfast and coffee after a hard night of partying.
Hangover helper. Mon.-Wed. 7am-3pm, Thurs.-Sat. 8am-9pm, Sun. 8:30am-9pm.
Under $7. No credit cards. Beer.
<H2>Deli
</H2><P><STRONG>Sam &amp; Andy's
<BR></STRONG>717 18th St., 524-9527
<BR>    11110 Kingston Pike , 675-4242
<BR>    This long standing establishment in the heart of UT deli-land is
the watermark
by which all other delis are judged. Home of the juicy Vol burger, and the
place to dine on game day. Mon.-Thurs. 7:30am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 7:30am-3am,
Sun. 7:30am-11pm. Under $7. No credit cards. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Selvador Deli
<BR></STRONG>715 17th Street, 522-FOOD
<BR>    This hip little joint serves everything from burgers and gourmet
pizzas
to pasta and vegetarian dishes. Located in the parking lot behind Cat's Records.
The spinach pizza rules. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-4am,
Sun. 11am-midnight. $5-$12. V/MC/D. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Vic &amp; Bill's
<BR></STRONG>1501 White Ave., 524-9863
<BR>    A great place to go for the Fort Sanders partier or the cost-conscious
UT law student. Choose from nine different cheeses for your sandwich. Interesting
late-night crowd. Mon.-Fri. 24 hours, Sat. &amp; Sun. 7am-6am. Under $7.
No credit cards. Beer only.
<H2>Indian
</H2><P><STRONG>Kashmir
<BR></STRONG>711 17th St., 524-1982
<BR>    Knoxville's only authentic Indian restaurant serves tandoori chicken,
exotic Indian breads, and complex curries that will make your mouth water.
Create your own good karma by ingesting their terrific korma. Mon.-Sat.
11:30am-3pm and 5pm-10pm, Sunday buffet noon-3pm. $7-12. V/MC/D. Beer only.
<H2>Italian
</H2><P><STRONG>Best Italian
<BR></STRONG>2000 Cumberland Ave., 546-7170
<BR>    A casual dining experience specializing in pizza and pasta, all made
from
scratch, and baked in a stone oven. A large dining area, and electronic games
for the kids. Sun.-Tues. 11am-12am, Wed.-Sat. 11am-2am. Lunch under $7, dinner
$7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Mid-East
</H2><P><STRONG>Falafel Hut
<BR></STRONG>601 15th St., 522-4963
<BR>    Huge selection of delish specialties voted "Best Middle Eastern
Restaurant"
in our 1996 poll. Falafel, hummus, baba ganoush, tabbuoli are just the beginning.
Has a wide variety of imported and microbrewed beers. Mon.-Thurs. 9am-9pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 9am-10pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Fatoosh
<BR></STRONG>1903-05 Cumberland Ave., 637-0808
<BR>    All the best of the Middle East, in a friendly exciting atmosphere.
Sun.-Sat.
11am-10pm. Under $7. No credit cards, checks accepted. No alcohol.
<H2>Pizza
</H2><P><STRONG>The Pizza and Sandwich Emporium
<BR></STRONG>On UT Campus at Shelbourne Towers, 525-4960
<BR>    Food for thought for the hungry scholar. The Emporium has salads,
burgers
and dogs, hot and cold subs, and of course, pizza. All their pizzas are extra
large 16" with thin, New York--style crust. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-12pm, Fri. &amp;
Sat. 11am-2am. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Selvador Deli
<BR></STRONG>715 17th Street, 522-FOOD
<BR>    This hip little joint serves everything from burgers and gourmet
pizzas
to pasta and vegetarian dishes. Located in the parking lot behind Cat's Records.
The spinach pizza rules. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-4am,
Sun. 11am-midnight. $5-$12. V/MC/D. Beer only.
<H2>Wings
</H2><P><STRONG>Spicy's
<BR></STRONG>1800 Cumberland Ave., 523-4723
<BR>    Buffalo wings and cold beer: a match made in heaven. Mon.-Wed. 11am-1am,
Thurs. &amp; Sat. 11am-1:30am, Sun. 11am-11pm. (Summer hours may vary.) Under
$7. V/MC/D. Beer only.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
