<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_downtown.gif" ALT="Downtown" WIDTH="181" HEIGHT="29">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>The Bistro
<BR></STRONG>807 S. Gay, 544-0537
<BR>For lunch or dinner, an escape for the downtown professional and/or Bijou
concert-goer, with fresh fish brought in daily and a variety of outstanding
pasta dishes. Weekday happy hour is from 4-7pm and features 99-cent draft
beer and ten-cent wings, and they're open before and after all Bijou events
(excluding Sunday matinees). Mon.-Fri. 11am-9pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<H2>BBQ
</H2><P><STRONG>Calhoun's
<BR></STRONG>400 Neyland Dr., 673-3355
<BR>       While you're enjoying the delicious barbecued ribs that were voted
"Best
Ribs" in Knoxville in our '96 Readers Poll (for the second year in a row),
take in the fabulous river front view (or lakefront view, or, well, interstate
view). Don't miss such instant Knoxville classics as spinach Maria, white
bean chili, and the original onion loaf. Mon.-Fri. 11am-10pm, Sat.-Sun.
11am-11pm. $7-$17. V/MC/AE/DC/D/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Cafe
</H2><P><STRONG>Cafe Max
<BR></STRONG>4 Market Square, 546-6717
<BR>       The cafe formerly known as the "Uptown Bakery" offers tasty, healthy
lunches
and sugary treats for the downtowner. A diet chicken salad to cry for, and
other lite and vegetarian treats. Under $7. Mon.-Fri. 7:30am-3pm. V/MC. No
alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Crescent Moon Cafe
<BR></STRONG>705 Market St., 637-9700
<BR>       A breath of fresh food for downtown lunchers, Crescent Moon offers
homemade
bread and pastries, low-fat soups and excellent sandwiches. Partner chefs
Terri and Michelle have a flair for the healthy and unique. Mon.-Fri.
7:30am-2:30pm, closed Sat. &amp; Sun. Under $7. No credit cards, checks accepted.
No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Pete's Cafe
<BR></STRONG>603 Main St., 525-8816
<BR>       Old-time favorite Pete's Coffee Shop extends its reach into downtown's
Medical Arts building with a slightly more refined menu of down-home favorites.
Beef tips and noodles, anyone? Mon.-Fri. 6am-2pm. Under $7. No credit cards.
No alcohol.
<H2>Coffee Shop
</H2><P><STRONG>Line's Sweets and Eats
<BR></STRONG>412 Clinch Ave., 523-2414
<BR>Coffee, short-order food, and friendly staff. Have the Line's supreme
on fresh baked bread, or try one of the hot-plate lunches. And don't forget
to pick up a thumb-print cookie on the way out the door. Mon.-Fri. 7am-2pm.
Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Pete's Coffee Shop
<BR></STRONG>428 Union Ave., 523-2860
<BR>    Traditional diner that serves up sass along with its down-home Southern
cooking. Sit at the counter, and don't miss the lemon ice box pie. Mon.-Fri.
6am-2pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<H2>Continental
</H2><P><STRONG>Country Garden
<BR></STRONG>500 Hill Ave., Hyatt Regency, 637-1234
<BR>    Fine dining in a vast indoor courtyard. Breakfast, lunch and dinner
menus
run the gamut from staples and standards to original flourishes like papaya
relish served alongside the seared salmon filet. The Cuisine Naturelle logo
marks items prepared from fresh, low-fat ingredients. Sun.-Thurs 6:30am-11pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 6:30am-midnight. $12 and up. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer, wine liquor.
<P><STRONG>Regas
<BR></STRONG>318 N. Gay St., 637-9805
<BR>    A familiar favorite with a fresh new face. Regas has been remodeled,
but
continues to offer the superb service and fine dining experience East Tennesseans
have come to love. Still tops in town are the aged choice beef and fresh
seafood specials, and the fresh-baked breads and pastries. "The Gathering
Place" offers a more casual atmosphere these days, with live entertainment,
a lighter menu, and frequent drink specials. Mon.-Fri. 11am-10:30pm, Sat.
5pm-12:30am. Sun. 11:30am-2pm. Lunch $7 and up, dinner $12 and up. V/MC/AE/DC/CB.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Deli
</H2><P><STRONG>Goldie's
<BR></STRONG>420 Union Ave., 971-1010
<BR>    Previously Sampson's, this quaint little lunch spot with the '40s
decor
offers your favorite deli sandwiches steamed to perfection. Mon.-Fri. 8am-7pm.
Under $7. No credit cards.
<P><STRONG>Harold's
<BR></STRONG>131 S. Gay St., 523-5315
<BR>    Huge kosher sandwiches for the hungry-man appetite. Voted "Best Deli"
with the "Best Sandwiches" by Metro Pulse readers, Harold's is a 50-year
Gay Street institution--a genuine Jewish delicatessen right here in Knoxville.
Treasure it. Mon.-Fri. 6am-4:30pm, Sat. 6am-4pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D/DC.
Beer only.
<H2>Diner
</H2><P><STRONG>Joann's
<BR></STRONG>205 Union Ave., 521-6844
<BR>    Wash down your breakfast with a beer at this beloved downtown diner.
Mon.-Thurs. 6:30am-7pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 6:30am-11pm. Under $7. No credit
cards of checks. Beer only.
<H2>Lunch
</H2><P><STRONG>A.J.'s
<BR></STRONG>912 S. Gay St., 594-1597/1213
<BR>    Downtown lunch in a hurry, with a tasty selection of sandwiches,
salads
and soups. They also cater. Mon.-Fri. 7am-2pm. Under $7. No credit cards.
No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Froggy's
<BR></STRONG>718 S. Gay St., 637-3764
<BR>    Comfort lunches of the blue-plate-special sort. Seventeen vegetables
a
day (!), and don't forget their famous addictive "swamp tea." Mon.-Fri.
11am-2:30pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Garo's
<BR></STRONG>722 S. Gay St., 524-1374
<BR>    A great place to grab a biscuit in the morning. For lunch try a hot
dog--the
best slaw 'n' chili dog in town (cheese optional)--or the marinated chicken
sandwich. Fresh salads, daily soups and blue-plate specials on Tuesday and
Thursday. Mon.-Fri. 7am-4pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Gus's Restaurant
<BR></STRONG>506 S. Gay St., 525-9338
<BR>    Downtown's largest restaurant serves a variety of home-cooked specials.
Says the management: "We treat all customers as guests in our own home."
Mon.-Fri. 6:30am-3:30pm. Under $7 No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>J. Scott's
<BR></STRONG>2 Market Square, 521-7238
<BR>    Just recently taking up residence at one of Knoxville's primo
people-watching
locations, J. Scott's offers quick and tasty lunch items for downtown folks.
A variety of salads, fresh-baked potatoes, topped the way you like'em, and
daily specials make for fast food that's better than fast food. The hefty
charbroiled Market Burger comes recommended. Mon.-Fri. 7:30am-2:30pm, closed
Sat. &amp; Sun. Under $7. Cash only. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>The Lunchbox
<BR></STRONG>Plaza Tower, Gay St., 525-7421
<BR>    6701 Baum Dr., 584-7682<BR>This longtime favorite offers sandwiches, soups and assorted daily specials
(spinach enchiladas!). Excellent desserts, especially the infamous chocolate
chess pie. Mon.-Fri. 11am-2pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Perry's on the Square
<BR></STRONG>Market Square Mall , 637-4455
<BR>    Healthy, fresh assorted ethnic, homestyle, and vegetarian lunches
for
the adventurous downtown diner. Incredible salads, homemade soups and desserts,
and the most affordable quality seafood in town on Wednesdays. Mon.-Fri.
11am-2:30pm. Lunch under $7. V/MC. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>The Soup Kitchen
<BR></STRONG>1 Market Square Mall, 546-4212
<BR>    The perfect lunch for a cold-and-rainy day. Try anything from broccoli
cheddar to gratin savoyard soup. Yum! Voted "Best Soup" in Knoxville by our
readers. Mon.-Fri. 11am-2pm. Under $7. Checks accepted. No credit cards.
No alcohol.
<H2>Pizza
</H2><P><STRONG>Tomato Head
<BR></STRONG>Market Square Mall, 637-4067
<BR>    This garlic lovers' haven was voted to have the "Best Pizza" and
to be
the "Best Lunch Spot" in both our '95 and '96 reader's poll...and for good
reasons. Exotic homemade pizzas, amazing sandwiches and vegetarian specialties.
Their fresh salads topped with imaginative dressings, earned them the "Best
Salad" vote in the '96 poll. The calzone is hands-down the best around. Lunch
Mon.-Fri. 11am-2:30pm, dinner Fri. &amp; Sat. 5:30pm-11pm. $7-$12. AE/checks.
Beer only.
<H2>Seafood
</H2><P><STRONG>Chesapeake's
<BR></STRONG>500 Henley St., 673-3433
<BR>    Savor the fresh seafood (flown in weekly) that was voted "Best Seafood"
in our '96 Readers Poll in an atmosphere reminiscent of the Chesapeake Bay.
Featuring Maryland crab cakes, Alaskan king crab, and live Maine lobster.
Mon.-Thurs. 4:30pm -10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 4:30pm-11pm. Dinner over $18.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Steak
</H2><P><STRONG>Butcher Shop
<BR></STRONG>801 W. Jackson Ave., 637-0204
<BR>    Thick, juicy steaks are the specialty of the house. Cook it yourself,
or have them do it for you. Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm,
Sun. 4pm-10pm. $12-18+. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
