<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_oldcity.gif" ALT="Old City" WIDTH="134" HEIGHT="32">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>Manhattan's
<BR></STRONG>101 S. Central Ave., 525-4463
<BR>Regular menu favorites include Philly cheese steak, fish and chips, and
a good selection of vegetarian items. Feast on the specialty of the house,
the Old City Reuben: corned beef, turkey, Swiss cheese, sauerkraut, Russian
dressing and Dijon mustard on grilled pumpernickel. Now open for Sunday champagne
brunch. Mon.-Sun. 11am-3pm , Tues &amp; Thurs. 11am-12am, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-3am. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Burgers
</H2><P><STRONG>Hooray's
<BR></STRONG>106 S. Central		546-6729
<BR>       Cavernous sports bar with excellent soups, salads and traditional
meat-and-potatoes fare--voted the "Best Sports Bar" in Knoxville in our reader's
poll twice running, for all the right reasons. Wear orange. Mon.-Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. Noon-3am. Under $12. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Cafe
</H2><P><STRONG>Amsterdam Cafe
<BR></STRONG>102 Central St. , 523-2437
<BR>       A comfortable cafe/pub in the heart of the Old City with high
tables and
hardwood floors. Try the gourmet pizzas, turkey wraps, or the black bean
and veggie quesidillas. With over 100 different bottled beers to choose from,
and twenty on tap, it's no wonder it's been dubbed the "Best Beer Selection"
in town by our readers. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-?, Fri &amp; Sat. 11am-3am, Sun.
6pm-12am. Under $7. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Blue Moon Bakery &amp; Cafe
<BR></STRONG>125 Jackson Ave., 546-0332
<BR>       A Parisian style bakery/cafe in the Old City. Twenty-six variaties
of
fresh hearth-baked breads, made on site, used for the specialty sandwiches.
Try the homemade soup or a gourmet salad. Save room for dessert. Mon.-Sat.
8am-8pm, closed Sundays. V/MC/personal checks. Beer and wine.
<H2>Cajun
</H2><P><STRONG>The Big Easy
<BR></STRONG>125 E. Jackson Ave., 523-7711
<BR>       Creative Cajun entrees, appetizers, soups and salads seasoned
for land-locked
taste buds. The whole menu--which naturally includes jambalaya,
&eacute;touff&eacute;e and scads of seafood--can be spiced to order. Dinner
Mon.-Thurs. 4:30pm-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 4:30-?. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<H2>Coffee Shop
</H2><P><STRONG>Java
<BR></STRONG>109-1/2 S. Central Ave., 525-1600
<BR>    5115 Homberg Dr., 558-0100
<BR>    Intimate but sociable coffeehouse in the heart of the Old City. According
to the '96 Readers Poll, once again, it's the "Best Coffeehouse" with the
"Best Coffee" and "Best Desserts" in Knoxville. Check out the smoke-free
side, and the up-to-the-second fashions modeled by the non-stop parade of
caffeine-mad club kids. Sun.-Thurs. 8am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 8am-2am. Under
$7. V/MC/AE/PC/D. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>JFG Coffee House
<BR></STRONG>132 W. Jackson Ave., 525-0012
<BR>JFG, Knoxville's claim to the coffee hall of fame, has its own entry
in the coffee shop sweepstakes. With its high ceilings, book-lined walls,
and
unpretentious atmosphere, it's the perfect place for fresh-brewed coffee,
inviting desserts, and fresh bread. Closed Sunday and Monday. Tues.-Thurs.
9am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 9am-12:30am. Under $7. V/MC/AE. No alcohol.
<H2>Continental
</H2><P><STRONG>Lucille's
<BR></STRONG>106 N. Central Ave., 546-3742
<BR>    Drinks, jazz, and an elegant menu, all dished up in a classy-but-funky
Old City setting. Try the special crab-artichoke dip or beer-steamed shrimp.
New to the menu are pistachio salmon, Chilean sea bass, poppyseed duck and
even more vegetarian entrees. Sun. and Tues.-Thurs. 6pm-10pm, Fri.-Sat. 6pm-2am,
closed Mon. $12 and up. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Fondue
</H2><P><STRONG>The Melting Pot
<BR></STRONG>111 N. Central Ave., 971-5400
<BR>    The Melting Pot is like no other Knoxville restaurant. No dining
and dashing
here; by ordering, you embark upon a unique and intimate two-hour experience.
The salads and wine list are about as good as they get, but the fondue is
the centerpiece of every meal. Meats, cheeses, vegetables, fruits and breads
are prepared at your table, where you then cook them either in the traditional
peanut oil or the lighter Court Bouillon. Over $18. Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-11pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-midnight. Reservations recommended. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<H2>Japanese
</H2><P><STRONG>Tomo
<BR></STRONG>112 S. Central Ave., 546-3308
<BR>    Knoxville's only full-menu Japanese restaurant with a sushi bar and
a
genuine karaoke scene. If sushi isn't your style, try the yaki soba noodles
(panfried noodles with chicken and veggies) or the fried tempura. Sun. and
Tues.-Thurs. 5pm-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-10pm. $7-$15. V/MC/AE. Beer
only.
<H2>Mexican
</H2><P><STRONG>Amigo's
<BR></STRONG>116 S. Central Ave., 546-9505
<BR>    Complete Mexican fare with a Texas twist. Their pulled barbecue will
melt
in your mouth. Tasty lunch buffets specials. Live music on weekends, and
a very happy happy hour. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm,
Sun. 3pm-9pm. Under $12. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Vegetarian
</H2><P><STRONG>All Night Eggplant
<BR></STRONG>105B W. Jackson Ave., 521-8077
<BR>    An eclectic cafe and coffee house offering vegetarian and vegan fare.
They've substituted the meat, but not the taste. BGH-free milk products leave
plenty to choose from if you're following a special diet. Can't make it for
dinner? Stop by for after hour appetizers, drinks or coffee. (It's roasted
weekly). Live music Fri. &amp; Sat. Poetry reading Wed. Musicians open mic
Sundays. Mon., Wed., Thurs. 8am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 9am-12am, Sun. 9am-8pm.
Lunch starts at $2.50, Dinner under $8.50. VI/MC/D/AE/DC. Microbrew beers
only.
<P><STRONG>Tjaarda's
<BR></STRONG>118 S. Central Ave., 637-8702
<BR>    Veteran Knoxville chef Mike Tjaarda creates vegetarian and seafood
specialties
to fill what was once a glaring void in the local restaurant scene. Try the
black bean and spinach lasagna, crab cakes, or pierogies with a bottle from
their inexpensive wine list. Lunch: Mon.-Fri. 11am-2pm, Dinner: Mon.-Thurs.
5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer and wine.
<H2>Wings
</H2><P><STRONG>bw3
<BR></STRONG>109 N. Central Ave., 522-4293
<BR>    In case you haven't guessed from the initials, Buffalo-style chicken
wings
are the specialty of the house. They also offer salads, grilled items from
"Southwest of the border," and Knoxville's largest selection of draft beers.
Voted "Best Wings" by our readers one more time. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-2:30am,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
