<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_north.gif" ALT="North Knoxville" WIDTH="273" HEIGHT="27">
<H2>Burgers
</H2><P><STRONG>Litton's
<BR></STRONG>2803 Essary Dr.		688-0429
<BR>       Burgers worth waiting in line for--they were voted "Best Burger"
in town
in our '96 Readers Poll. Supporting roles played by the incredible blue-plate
lunches and delicious homemade desserts have made Litton's a Knoxville
institution. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm. $7-12. Cash
and local checks. BYOB.
<P><STRONG>Sassy Ann's
<BR></STRONG>820 N. Fourth Ave.	525-5839
<BR>       Situated in an old Victorian home, this Fourth &amp; Gill neighborhood
restaurant and pub has got to be the comfiest spot in town in which to belly
up to the bar. Relax on the new patio and enjoy cool outdoor drink specials.
Also, their burgers are HUGE. Tues.-Sun. (deck and downstairs) 3pm-3am, upstairs
bar opens at 7pm. Closed Mondays. V/MC/AE/D. Beer.
<H2>Cafe
</H2><P><STRONG>Fountain City Creamery
<BR></STRONG>114 Hotel Ave., 688-4607
<BR>       Fountain City's favorite treatery is not just for ice cream anymore.
Warm
your tummy with homemade soups, grilled burgers, sandwiches and coffee.
Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm, Sun. 3pm-9pm. Under $7.
No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Kitts Market Cafe
<BR></STRONG>Knox County Farmers' Mkt., 522-7311
<BR>       This family owned and operated cafe has all the goodies you might
find
at a country fair. Have some fried bologna or pinto beans and cornbread.
Mon.-Sat. 10am-5pm, Sun. noon-5pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<H2>Chinese
</H2><P><STRONG>Real Peking
<BR></STRONG>736 Broadway, 546-9973
<BR>       Vast menu and buffet featuring Peking duck, Mongolian beef, and
seafood
delight. Chef Peter Wong will gladly prepare "any special order you can think
of." Can you resist such a challenge? Lunch Mon.-Sat. 11am-3pm, dinner
Mon.-Thurs. 4:30pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 4:30pm-10:30pm. Under $7-$12.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. No alcohol.
<H2>Continental
</H2><P><STRONG>Litton's Back Room
<BR></STRONG>2803 Essary Rd., 687-8788
<BR>    The former Fountain Room still offers huge steaks and fresh seafood--just
add gourmet pizza and a new 25-oz. prime rib to the menu. Don't forget about
the creative pasta entrees and the house-baked bread and desserts. Tues.-Sat.
5pm until they kick you out. $7-$18. V/MC/AE. Beer and wine only.
<P><STRONG>Wallaby's Restaurant &amp; Pub
<BR></STRONG>902-1/2 Kermit Dr. , 281-2228
<BR>    Vegemite, pavlova and meat pies served along with some plain 'ol
Yankee
food for the unadventurous. Distract our young 'uns with trivia and Pictionary
cards, and crayons for writing on the butcher-paper tablecloths. It's a g'deal,
mate. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10:30pm, closed Sunday.
$5-$12. V/MC/D. Beer and liquor.
<H2>Diner
</H2><P><STRONG>Glenwood Sandwich Shop
<BR></STRONG>1319 N. 6th Ave., 525-1406
<BR>    A true neighborhood gathering place that offers the finest in fine
diner
fare. Mon.-Fri. Closed weekends. 7am-8pm. Under $7. No credit cards. Beer
only.
<P><STRONG>Lorrie's Southern Grill
<BR></STRONG>3553 N. Broadway, 687-0383
<BR>    This quaint and comfortable restaurant (formerly a drug store) feels
like
it's 80 years old, right off the cover of a vintage Saturday Evening Post.
The meals--from fried bologna to chuck wagon steak--are homemade and ordered
plate-lunch style, Jello and macaroni salad on the side. Mon.-Sat. 6am-8pm,
Sun. 6am-3pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<H2>Italian
</H2><P><STRONG>Fazoli's
<BR></STRONG>4721 Old Broadway, 688-1679
<BR>    Proof positive that fast food can be good food. Pizza, lasagna, and
a
variety of pastas with fresh sauces served quick. bonus: garlic breadsticks
with every meal. Mon.-Sun. 10:30am-10pm. Under $7. Checks. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Louis Inn
<BR></STRONG>4626 Old Broadway, 688-4121
<BR>    A North Knoxville tradition. Amazing sampler platter. Lots of sandwiches
and pizza. Try their homemade ravioli. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp;
Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12. No credit cards. Beer only.
<H2>Malaysian
</H2><P><STRONG>Malaysia Restaurant
<BR></STRONG>6761 Clinton Hwy,
<BR>    Wal-Mart Shopping Center, 974-3333
<BR>    Offering truly unique Asian cuisine, this surprising restaurant has
a
full Malaysian menu plus many Chinese staples. Try their great noodle dishes
such as char kway teow (fried rice noodles in a brown sauce), seafood such
as Malaysia honey shrimp, or their coconut cream curries. Mon-Thurs. 11am-9pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm, Sun noon-9pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<H2>Mexican
</H2><P><STRONG>El Chico
<BR></STRONG>116 Cedar Lane, 687-4242
<BR>Tex-mex-o-rama. One of Knoxville's best-kept secrets, and a nice alternative
to standard Mexican fare. Try the spinach quesadillas. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>La Carretta
<BR></STRONG>4011 N. Broadway, 689-4631
<BR>    Authentic, low-priced Mexican food in the heart of North Knoxville.
Watch
out for the live mariachi band they feature occasionally. Lunch Mon.-Fri.
11am-2:30pm, Sun. 11:30am-2pm, dinner Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-10:30pm, Fri. 5pm-11pm,
Sat. 11:30am-11pm, Sun. 5pm-9pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Pizza
</H2><P><STRONG>Cicero's Pizza
<BR></STRONG>6915 Maynardville Hwy., 922-3360
<BR>    Relax and enjoy award-winning pizza (and/or lasagna, spaghetti, salads
and subs) on Cicero's covered outdoor patio. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri.
&amp; Sat. 11am-11pm, Sun. noon-10pm. $7-$12. V/MC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Louis Original Drive In
<BR></STRONG>4624 Old Broadway, 688-4121
<BR>    This classic North Knoxville destination offers "fresh Italian made
pizza"--phone orders ready in 10 minutes. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp;
Sat. 11am-11pm. MC/V/AE. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Marcus' Pizza
<BR></STRONG>5100 N. Broadway , 687-9696
<BR>    The fresh and handmade ingredients at Marcus' make for the best pizza
in Knoxville ("...if not the world," says manager Joe Caldwell). They've
got vegetarian pies and a daily two-slice special. Open Sundays for FOOTBALL!
Tues.-Thurs. 11am-9:30pm. Fri. &amp; Sat. 11pm-midnight. No delivery. No
credit cards. Checks accepted. Beer only.
<H2>Steak
</H2><P><STRONG>Sagebrush Steakhouse
<BR></STRONG>110 Cedar Lane, 687-1650
<BR>    Low-priced steakhouse offering affordable hand cut steaks. Lots o'
free
peanuts, but watch out--the floor is covered with shells. Banquet room available
for private parties. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12+.
V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Vietnamese
</H2><P><STRONG>T. Ho
<BR></STRONG>815 Merchants Dr., 688-5815
<BR>    Vietnamese specialties and incredible spring rolls. Try the eggless
crepe
with shrimp. Tues.-Fri. 11am-9:30pm, Sat. 5pm-10pm, Sun. Noon-9pm. Under
$7. V/MC/AE. BYOB.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
