<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_south.gif" ALT="South Knoxville" WIDTH="265" HEIGHT="28">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>R.J.'S Courtyard
<BR></STRONG>3749 Airport Hwy., 970-7777
<BR>Tempting American cuisine in a relaxed tropical setting for the plane-weary
traveler. Try the garden burger or their dessert specialty: an ice cream
Idaho baked potato(?!). Sun.-Thurs. 11am-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10:30pm.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine coolers.
<H2>Cajun
</H2><P><STRONG>Bayou Bay
<BR></STRONG>7112 Chapman Hwy., 573-7936
<BR>       Knoxville's original source for Cajun cookin'. All kinds of yummy
seafood.
Try the steamed crayfish, Bayou Bay oysters or the steamed snow crab legs.
The grilled amberjack is especially noteworthy. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri.
11am-10pm, Sat. 12pm-10pm. $7-$12. V/MC/D/DC. Beer only.
<H2>Burgers
</H2><P><STRONG>Rally's Hamburgers
<BR></STRONG>2320 Chapman Hwy.	573-8567
<BR>       The fastest, the cheapest, and some of the tastiest burgers among
the
fast-food joints. Mon.-Sun. 10am-11pm. Way under $7. No credit cards. No
alcohol.
<H2>Chinese
</H2><P><STRONG>Hong Kong
<BR></STRONG>6518 Chapman Hwy., 609-2377
<BR>       A South Knoxville cousin to the venerable West Knox institution
Canton,
Hong Kong carries many of the same menu items. This means specialties you
won't find anywhere else, including Hong Kong Bird's Nest (served on a fried
potato "nest"), Hong Sui Dow Foo, or Hong Kong Chow Wonton (a variety of
meats adorned with fried won ton dumplings). They also have a few of Canton's
dim sum selections, including the chicken curry turnovers. For dessert, try
the fried sesame balls with red bean paste. Tues.-Sun., 11am-9:30pm; closed
Mon. Most entrees under $7. V/MC/D/AE
<P><STRONG>The Ming Tree
<BR></STRONG>2754 Alcoa Hwy., 984-3888
<BR>       Tucked away on the Airport Motor Mile, the Ming Tree offers an
elegant
atmosphere and fine Oriental cuisine. Try the tasty Thai selections for dinner.
Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. Lunch under $5, dinner
$5-$12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>New China Town
<BR></STRONG>2619 Chapman Hwy., 577-0593
<BR>       Huge Oriental lunch-a-thon. Lunch everyday 11am-3:30pm, lunch
buffet Sun.-Fri.
11am-2:30pm, dinner Sun.-Thurs. 3:30pm-9:00pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 3:30pm-10:30pm,
dinner buffet Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-9pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-9:30pm Under $7.
V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Szechuan Garden
<BR></STRONG>4211 Chapman Hwy., 579-0889
<BR>       A South Knoxville gem that offers high quality food at great prices.
Real
Szechuan-style available--just ask the chefs to make it for you as they'd
make it for themselves. Do not miss the dee-diddly-licious hot and sour soup.
Lunch Mon.-Sun. 11am-4pm, dinner Mon.-Thurs. 4pm-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
4pm-10:30pm, Sun. 4pm-9pm. Under $12. V/MC/AE/D. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Wong's Dynasty
<BR></STRONG>6135 Chapman Hwy., 573-0497
<BR>       Low-key, affordable Chinese food in a brand-new restaurant that
retains
the funky aura of its predecessor, Happy Palace. Still on the menu is the
legendary Peking duck, but sample such newcomers as lemon chicken, curried
shrimp, and green onion pancakes. Daily buffet. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri.
&amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. Lunch under $7, dinner $7-12. V/MC/AE. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Wong's Palace
<BR></STRONG>4009 Chapman Hwy., 573-4580
<BR>       Noted for its Peking duck. Check out the yummy buffet. Sun.-Thurs.
4:30pm-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 4:30pm-10pm. $7-$12 and up. V/MC/AE/DC/D.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Cajun
</H2><P><STRONG>The Big Easy
<BR></STRONG>125 E. Jackson Ave., 523-7711
<BR>       Creative Cajun entrees, appetizers, soups and salads seasoned
for land-locked
taste buds. The whole menu--which naturally includes jambalaya,
&eacute;touff&eacute;e and scads of seafood--can be spiced to order. Dinner
Mon.-Thurs. 4:30pm-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 4:30-?. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<H2>Deli
</H2><P><STRONG>The Country Deli
<BR></STRONG>5334 E. John Sevier Hwy., 524-9171
<BR>    Knoxville's best-kept deli secret. Mon.-Fri. 6am-6pm, Sat. &amp;
Sun.
6am-2pm. Under $7. No credit cards. Beer for carry out only.
<H2>Family
</H2><P><STRONG>King Tut's
<BR></STRONG>4123 Martin Mill Pike, 573-6021
<BR>    Masterminded by Mo Girgis, King Tut's is one of Knoxville's most
original
restaurants. The fruits and vegetables are fresh, nothing is fried, and the
dinner theme is different every night. Monday is pasta night, Tuesday "Grill
night", Wednesday is Egyptian night, Saturday is "Candlelight Dinner Night"
(linen tablecloths and "every woman gets a rose"). Try the falafel for lunch.
Sunday brunch: 10:30am-2pm. Coming soon: open Sunday for dinner: Vegetarian
night. Mon.-Sat. 6am-8pm. Under $7-$12. Cash and personal checks accepted.
BYOB.
<H2>Mexican
</H2><P><STRONG>Polo Mexican
<BR></STRONG>7317 Chapman Hwy., 573-4377
<BR>    A big taste of Mexico, with the look, the feel and the smell. Best
known
for the daily lunch buffet for $3.99, the regular menu is just as tempting.
Mon.-Fri. 11am-10pm, Sat &amp; Sun. 12pm-10pm. Under $7. V/MC. Beer only.
<H2>Pizza
</H2><P><STRONG>DeAngelo's Pizza Express
<BR></STRONG>4509 Chapman Hwy., 579-3038
<BR>    Finally--some non-chain pizza for hungry South Knoxvillians. Try
the
"take-'n-bake" pizza. Mon.-Sat. 11am-10pm. Under $7-$12. Checks. No alcohol.
<H2>Steak
</H2><P><STRONG>Ye Olde Steak House
<BR></STRONG>6838 Chapman Hwy., 577-9328
<BR>    Funky, fun South Knoxville favorite since 1968, voted "Best Steak"
in
our Reader's Poll. For beef purists. Check out the back of your chair for
wise advice. Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm. $7-$18 and up.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer and BYOB.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
