<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_west.gif" ALT="West Knoxville" WIDTH="249" HEIGHT="27">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>Applewood's
</STRONG><BR>West Knoxville, 996-1160
<BR>Americana, country cuisine for breakfast, lunch or dinner. Highlights
include specialty salads, steaks and ribs. Breakfast with all the fixings.
Although they don't open until mid-October, plans include lake views and
a landscaped boardwalk. Group and banquet facilities available. Hours not
yet set, but they'll be open year round.
<P><STRONG>Bullfeathers
<BR></STRONG>10535 Kingston Pike, 690-1786
<BR>Beef (that's the bull) and chicken (that's the feathers). Try their homemade
chicken cordon bleu or baby back ribs. Karaoke Thurs. &amp; Fri.; live
entertainment Sat. night. Lunch Tues.-Fri. 11am-3pm, dinner Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm, closed Sun. Lunch under $5, dinner $7-$12.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer and wine coolers; bring the rest if you like.
<P><STRONG>Ivory's
<BR></STRONG>4705 Old Kingston Pike, 588-6023
<BR>A "nice quiet piano lounge" with weekly jazz including appearances by
Spencer Cordon and the David Binkley Duo. Entertainment starts at 8pm Wed.
&amp; Thurs.; Fri.-Sat. the music starts at 9pm. Prime rib and dinner specials.
Mon., Wed. &amp; Thurs. 11am-10pm., Tues. 11am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. 3pm-midnight. Lunch under $7, dinner $7-$12. MC/V/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>McGuffey's
<BR></STRONG>100 N. Seven Oaks Dr., , 691-8914
<BR>Windsor Sq.
<BR>A light, healthy menu is now available, but their HUGE cheese sticks
are
an absolute must. Try the blackened Cajun specialties. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-11pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-12pm. Lunch under $7, Dinner $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Miami Subs Grill
<BR></STRONG>9739 Kingston Pike, 691-1266
<BR>The timing of fast food with the feel of a full-service restaurant. Chow
down on a cheese steak sub or gyro, and top it off with some frozen yogurt.
But remember: the indoor playground is for kids only. Sun-Thurs. 10:30am-12am,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 10:30am-1am. Under $7. V/MC/AE. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>The Mill
<BR></STRONG>Western Plaza, 588-0080
<BR>Brewery, bakery, restaurant...what else could you want? The muffins are
good--the guilt-free chocolate is a low-fat indulgence. The food is great--try
the fabulous wild mushroom meatloaf or the grilled pork loin in Jack Daniel's
mustard cream sauce. But the real standout is the beer--have the harvest
gold, the magic brew, the Rocky Top red, or the studly stout. Liquid refreshment
at its best. Mon.-Wed. 11am-11pm, Thurs.-Sun. 11am-1am. $7-$15. V/MC/AE.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Rafferty's Restaurant &amp; Bar
<BR></STRONG>8906 Kingston Pike , 539-1323
<BR>Self-dubbed "The American Grille," Rafferty's cooks its American fare
over an open hickory wood fire. And, refreshingly, all its salads are made
fresh to order. The atmosphere is upbeat, with an abundance of plants and
a soundtrack featuring the ever-popular hits of the '50s, '60s, and '70s.
Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $6-$17. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Soup Kitchen
<BR></STRONG>9246 Park West Blvd., 539-6500
<BR>This West Knoxville offshoot of one of downtown's favorite lunch spots
offers the same array of fine soups (voted "Best" in our Reader's Poll),
and dinner to boot. Mon.-Fri. 11am-8pm, Sat. &amp; Sun. 11am-2pm. Under $7.
<P><STRONG>T.G.I. Friday's
<BR></STRONG>1613 Downtown West Blvd., 690-3273
<BR>All the classics (burgers, fries) plus a few wonderfully unexpected surprises
like the baked brie with pesto and roasted garlic. For the light eater, they
offer a wide variety of salads and light items. They claim their happy hour
is the best in town, and won "Best Appetizers" in our '96 Reader's Poll.
Happy Hour Mon.-Fri. 4pm-7pm, $1 drafts, and $1 off all mixed drinks. Sun.-Thurs.
11am-12am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-3am. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>BBQ
</H2><P><STRONG>Calhoun's BBQ &amp; Brew
<BR></STRONG>6515 Kingston Pike, 673-3377
<BR>       This youngest branch of the Calhoun family tree has all that you've
come
to expect from its cousins: consistently good sandwiches, grilled chicken
and steaks, ribs and pork, and salads. But with the addition of an in-house
brewery, the specialty of this house is the handcrafted brew. Another Thunder
Road, anyone? Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight, Sun.
11am-9pm. $7-$12. V/ MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Corky's Ribs &amp; B.B.Q.
<BR></STRONG>260 North Peters Rd., 690-3137
<BR>       Ribs, ribs, and more ribs. Be sure to try them both wet and dry.
Memphis
made this place an institution, so no wonder their famous B.B.Q. pork and
B.B.Q. sauce was voted #1 in Knoxville in our Reader's Poll. Also, drop by
for happy hour: Mon.-Fri. from 3pm to 8pm and all day Sat. &amp; Sun. Sun.-Thurs.
11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$14. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Sarge's BBQ
<BR></STRONG>3506 Pleasant Ridge Rd., 544-1440
<BR>       Home-grown barbecue that has more than earned its devoted cult
following.
Don't leave without trying the authentic Virgin Island style ginger cakes.
Mon.-Wed. 10am-10pm, Thurs.-Sat. 10am-midnight. Closed Sunday. Under $7.
No alcohol.
<H2>Cafe
</H2><P><STRONG>Aubrey's Courthouse Cafe
<BR></STRONG>102 S. Campbell Station Rd. , 671-2233
<BR>       A pleasant surprise tucked away in Farragut. The usual surf and
turf,
but with a nice twist. The Firehouse pasta is a spicy treat--they take two
different kinds of chili and toss it with fettuccine. Mon.-Sun. 11am-10pm.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Courtyard Cafe
<BR></STRONG>4900 Chambliss Ave., 584-0091
<BR>       A true open-air cafe (yes, in a courtyard) that offers a nice
selection
of salads and sandwiches. Specials include the breast of chicken piccata.
Everything is HOMEMADE! Mon.-Thurs. 10am to 5pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 10am-10pm.
Lunch under $7, dinner under $13. MC/V/AE. Beer, wine.
<P><STRONG>Jason's Cafe
<BR></STRONG>2452 Sutherland Ave., 673-0770
<BR>       Light, tasty fare for the cost-conscious breakfast and lunch patron.
Mon.-Fri.
7am-4pm, Sat. 7am-3pm. Under $5. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Silver Spoon Cafe
<BR></STRONG>Gallery Shopping Ctr., 584-1066
<BR>       Superb soups and salads, excellent pasta dishes, the ultimate
chicken
pot pie, and desserts to die for, all served up in a splendid, cheery atmosphere.
Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $8-$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Slice of Life Cafe &amp; Bakery
<BR></STRONG>11426 Kingston Pike, 675-6560
<BR>       Even if you don't live in Farragut, it's well worth the trip.
Everything
is freshly made--and good luck making up your mind. Will it be pastries,
muffins, bagels, or croissant sandwiches for breakfast? For lunch, try the
chicken or tuna salad, or soup in a bread bowl. And don't miss East Tennessee's
first baked donut. Tues.-Sat. 6am-10pm, Sun. &amp; Mon. 6am-8pm. Under $7.
Cash or checks.
<H2>Chinese
</H2><P><STRONG>Asia
<BR></STRONG>Windsor Square, 693-7408
<BR>       Fine Chinese cuisine for the way-west crowd. Mon.-Sun. 11am-10pm.
Lunch
under $7, dinner under $12. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Bamboo Stix
<BR></STRONG>904 Merchants Dr, ., 281-8455
<BR>       Authentic Chinese cuisine that displays a wonderful flair for
interesting
sauces, and is presented beautifully--trust us, having your shrimp stir fry
served in a foil swan does make all the difference. Also, the steamed dumpling
are the best around. Lunch Mon.-Fri. 11am-2:30pm, Sat. &amp; Sun. 11:30am-3:45pm,
dinner Mon.-Sat. 4pm-10pm, Sun. 4pm-9:30pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. No checks.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Canton
<BR></STRONG>8515 Kingston Pike, 693-6424
<BR>       Home of dim sum (try the shrimp noodles or the curried chicken
turnovers)
on the weekends and some of the most authentic Chinese cuisine in town. A
willingness to experiment will be richly rewarded. Tues.-Sun. 11am-10pm.
Lunch under $5, dinner under $12. V/MC/D/DC. Beer and BYOB.
<P><STRONG>China House
<BR></STRONG>11509 Kingston Pike, 966-7918
<BR>       Exotic and authentic Chinese specialties ranging from wine-marinated
shrimp
to stuffed Bangkok chicken wings to Thai satay. A great place for culinary
thrill-seekers to dine with their friends who like sweet-and-sour standards.
Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm, Sun. 11am-9pm. $7-$12.
V/MC/D/AE. Beer and BYOB.
<P><STRONG>China Inn
<BR></STRONG>6450 Kingston Pike, 588-7815
<BR>       Upscale Chinese cuisine that is a longtime Knoxville favorite.
Lunch Mon.-Sat.
11am-3pm, dinner Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. 5pm-10:30pm. Lunch under $5,
dinner $12 and up. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>China Pearl
<BR></STRONG>11248 Kingston Pike, 966-6937
<BR>       Hefty portions that leave little room for the fortune cookie.
The chef's
specialties--Peking Duck and orange peel beef--are worth the visit. Mon.-Thurs.
11am-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm. Lunch under $6, dinner under $12.
V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Dragon Den
<BR></STRONG>10205A Kingston Pike, 691-4529
<BR>       With an extensive selection of Chinese staples (many with the
St. Mary's
"Eat Hearty" seal of approval), the Dragon Den's menu is highlighted by their
own special Peking duck, served with Mandarin pancakes and Hoisin sauce.
Also check out their sizable lunch menu. Sun.-Fri. 11am-10pm. Lunch is served
until 4pm. Lunch under $4.50, dinner under $10. D/V/MC. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Hunan Chinese Buffet &amp; Restaurant
<BR></STRONG>1645 Downtown West Blvd. , 694-5090
<BR>       Chef Robert Tsao has more than 25 years experience in Chinese
cooking,
and uses no MSG. Specialties include the sesame chicken, lo mein, and other
spicy dishes. Lunch Sun.-Fri. 11am-3pm, dinner Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-9pm, Fri.
&amp; Sat. 5pm-9:30pm. Under $7. V/MC/D/AE. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Keng's Garden
<BR></STRONG>4921 Homberg Dr., 588-3839
<BR>       A wide variety of Chinese, Hunan, Szechuan and Cantonese located
at the
old Merlot's building. Specialties include fresh steamed fish with ginger
and scallions. Come and relax on the patio open all summer. Weekends offer
Karaoke for those who like to sing. Or just come to dance and have a drink
at the bar. Sun.- Sat. 10:30am-10pm. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer, wine, alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Mandarin House
<BR></STRONG>8111 Gleason Dr., 694-0340
<BR>       A huge buffet of Oriental delights for both lunch and dinner.
Voted "Best
Buffet" in our '96 Reader's Poll (for the third year in a row!). The crispy
Szechuan green beans alone are worth the trip. Lunch Mon.-Fri. 11am-2:30pm,
Sat. &amp; Sun. 11am-4pm, dinner Sun.-Sat. 4:30pm-9:30pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>The Plum Tree
<BR></STRONG>7052 Kingston Pike, 588-2002
<BR>       A large selection of moderately priced Chinese specialties, from
Mandarin
to Cantonese. The funky, intimate atmosphere makes this a good, inexpensive
date place. Lunch Mon.-Sun. 11am-3pm, dinner Sun.-Thurs. 4pm-9:45pm, Fri.
&amp; Sat. 4pm-10:30pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Wok 'N' Roll
<BR></STRONG>213 N. Peters Road, 691-1055
<BR>       Choose your made-to-order entree from a list of chicken, pork,
beef, or
shrimp specialties. house favorites include the Sesame Chicken, Beef with
Broccoli or the General Tsao's Chicken. Daily all-you-can-eat buffet 11am-2:30pm
&amp; 5pm-8:30pm for a meager $4.50. Hours: Sun.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. &amp;
Sat. 11am-9:30pm. Under$7. Cash &amp; check only. No alcohol.
<H2>Coffee Shop
</H2><P><STRONG>Antiquities Coffee House
<BR></STRONG>7600 Kingston Pike,
<BR>West Town Mall, 690-5889
<BR>Relax with a gourmet cup of coffee while browsing the collection of old
and rare books available for purchase. They also brew up hot or cold tea,
cappuccino and espresso, to go with fresh baked pastries. Fresh made sweet
treats and baked goods, make great lunch time eats, available all day long.
They're across from Ruby Tuesday's in West Town Mall. Mon.-Sat. 8:30am-9:30pm,
Sun. 1:00pm-6:30pm. V/MC. Under $7. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Chaucer's Cup
<BR></STRONG>8513 Kingston Pike
<BR>(in Books-a-Million), 691-2665
<BR>Hanging out was never so fun. Buy some bargain books and read them over
a cappuccino or Torani-flavored Italian soda and a delicious homemade desserts.
Read, drink and watch their cable TV. Make a night out of it; they're open
later than the mall. Mon.-Sun. 9am-11pm. Under $7. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>CC Coffee's
<BR></STRONG>Western Plaza, 584-2902
<BR>A gourmet espresso bar with yummy desserts to go along with the coffee
and tea. They've also got neat coffee stuff for sale. Mon.-Thurs. 8am-6pm,
Fri. 8am-10pm, Sat. 10am-11pm, Sun. 10am-5pm. Under $7. V/MC. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Golden Roast
<BR></STRONG>825 Melrose Place, 544-1004
<BR>    Stop by for a cup of espresso and homemade desserts They also offer
specialty
smoothies, made with a variety of flavors, perfect for a hot day cool-down.
It's a smoker friendly espresso bar that provides room for round table meetings
and study groups, so bring a friend. Mon.-Fri. 7:30am-midnight, Sat.
9am-midnight, Sun. 10am-11pm. Under $7. Cash and checks only. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Hilton Head Ice Cream &amp; Coffee
<BR></STRONG>11110 Kingston Pike, 675-7707
<BR>    A casual ice cream parlor/coffee shop that offers bagels, muffins,
cakes
and pies. The perfect after-dinner treat. Mon.-Thurs. 7:30am-9pm, Fri.
7:30am-11pm, Sat. 9am-11pm and Sun. 12pm-9am. Under $7. No credit cards.
Personal checks accepted.
<H2>Continental
</H2><P><STRONG>By the Tracks Bistro
<BR></STRONG>130 Northshore Dr., 558-9500
<BR>    Under chef Bernadette Doyle, this new bistro has already made a name
for
itself among Knoxville's culinary destinations. For lunch, try grilled Portabella
mushroom sandwich served on Italian flatbread. At dinner, begin with the
low-country barbecued shrimp (served with molasses atop fluffy grits!). Move
onward to the pecan-crusted catfish or the magnificent honey and cider-cured
pork chops. Sigh. Lunch Mon.-Sat. 11am-2pm, dinner Mon.-Sat. 5pm-10pm, Closed
Sun. Lunch $8, dinner $13-$22. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer &amp; wine only.
<P><STRONG>The Chef Bistro &amp; Bakery
<BR></STRONG>5003 Kingston Pike, 584-1300
<BR>    French bistro cooking at its best--fresh ingredients simply prepared.
For lunch, the salad Nicoise is a delight, or try the seafood or chicken
or pasta specials. For dinner, the red snapper is tops. Menu changes daily
according to what ingredients are the freshest. Breakfast Tues.-Sat. 7:30-10am,
lunch Tues.-Sat. 11am-2:30pm, dinner Tues.-Sat. 6-10pm. Lunch $3.95-$8.95,
dinner $13-$18.95. No credit cards. Personal checks accepted. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Maple Grove Inn
<BR></STRONG>8800 Westland Dr., 690-9565
<BR>    An elegant country bed and breakfast right on the edge of town, Maple
Grove boasts a concise yet unique menu. Chef Curt Lockett is known for his
varied and creative stuffed filet mignon, and swordfish in blackberry barbecue
sauce. Whatever you order, the vanilla vinaigrette salad is a clue that you've
stumbled upon someplace special.
<BR>    Call for lunch information and arrangements. Dinner by reservation
only,
served Th.-Sat., 6:30pm-9pm. Closed Sun. Over $18. V/MC/AE, personal checks.
BYOB.
<P><STRONG>Michael's
<BR></STRONG>7049 Kingston Pike, 588-2455
<BR>    Upscale American, European and Mediterranean cuisines, with specialties
such as Steak Onassis (choice tenderloin topped with lobster, asparagus and
Swiss cheese) and capellini with mussels and spicy shrimp. Casual dining
atmosphere. Mon.-Fri. 5pm-11pm, Sat. &amp; Sun. 5pm-midnight. Lounge 4pm-2:30am.
$12-18. AE/V/DC/MC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Cuban
</H2><P><STRONG>Alex's Havana Cafe
<BR></STRONG>Homberg Place, 588-8681
<BR>    Cozy spot for authentic Cuban cuisine, including the now-famous Cuban
sandwiches and Knoxville's most fabulous black beans--fiber never tasted
so good. Lunch Mon.-Fri. 11:30am-2:30pm, Sat. noon-3pm, dinner Thurs.-Sat.
5:30pm-9pm. Under $7. V/MC. No alcohol.
<H2>Deli
</H2><P><STRONG>Alpine Bagel Company
<BR></STRONG>10400 Kingston Pike, 539-1838
<BR>    Home of gourmet and Old World--style bagels, Alpine (they changed
their
name from Aspen) also offers a full-service deli, gourmet coffees and a
cappuccino bar. Try the fragrant sun-dried tomato bagels, or, for a kick,
the jalapeno version. Mon.-Fri. 6am-6pm, Sat. 7am-3pm, Sun. 7:30am-2pm. Checks
or cash only.
<P><STRONG>Julio's Between the Buns
<BR></STRONG>Suburban Center, 693-5174
<BR>    Subs, pizzas and sports of all sorts. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-midnight,
Fri.
&amp; Sat. 11am-1am, Sun. noon-10:30pm. Under $12. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine,
liquor.
<P><STRONG>The Sandwich Emporium
<BR></STRONG>The Plaza, 693-4176
<BR>    Specializing in "Philly Style" sandwiches, the Emporium boasts an
expansive
menu of hot and cold subs, salads and their own special "Jersey Sloppy Joes."
Mon.-Fri. 11am-5pm, Sat. 12am-4pm, closed Sundays. Under $12 No credit cards.
No alcohol.
<H2>Diner
</H2><P><STRONG>Long's
<BR></STRONG>4604 Kingston Pike, 588-0581
<BR>    The last of a dying breed--the drug store diner with an old-fashioned
soda fountain your kids will love. Grilled cheese sandwich and vanilla coke,
anyone? Mon.-Fri. 8am-7pm, Sat. 8am-5pm. Under $7. V/MC. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>The Diner
<BR></STRONG>1612 Downtown West Blvd., 690-2345
<BR>    The Diner is considered by our readers to be "The Best Diner" in
town.
Formerly Litton's, they still feature first-rate burgers, blue-plate specials,
and tasty salads. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12.
V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Family
</H2><P><STRONG>Celebration Station
<BR></STRONG>400 N. Peters Rd., 539-2288
<BR>    Fun food to go along with those fun games, great place for birthday
parties.
Mon.-Thurs. 12am-9pm, Fri noon-11pm, Sat. 10am-11pm, Sun. 12am-9pm. Under
$7. V/MC/D. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Chuck E. Cheese
<BR></STRONG>7522 Kingston Pike, 588-5147
<BR>    A full-service family-style pizza restaurant that just happens to
harbor
a coin-operated entertainment arcade. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/personal checks. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Perkins Family Restaurant
<BR></STRONG>9507 Kingston Pike, 691-9255
<BR>    Traditional American fare: meat, fish &amp; chicken dishes, as well
as
sandwiches. Also has a bakery. Open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Under
$7. V/MC/AE/D. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Wright's Cafeteria
<BR></STRONG>5403 N. Middlebrook Pk., 588-2040
<BR>    This longtime cafeteria is a Knoxville landmark of genuine country
cooking.
Especially good desserts--the pies are outrageously good. Mon.-Fri. 11am-2pm,
Tue.-Thurs. 5pm-7:30pm. Under $7. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<H2>French
</H2><P><STRONG>The Orangery
<BR></STRONG>5412 Kingston Pike, 588-2964
<BR>    Luxuriate in the Old World atmosphere of Knoxville's only four-star
restaurant. Winner of AAA's four-diamond award, definitely la creme de la
creme. Nowhere else in town can you savor escargot in puff pastry, lobster
flamed in cognac, and wild boar. The wine list retains it's title as the
"Best" by our readers. Mon.-Fri. 11:30am-2:30pm, Sat. 6pm-11pm. Lunch $7-$12,
dinner $13-$23. Reservations encouraged. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Indian
</H2><P><STRONG>Cafe India
<BR></STRONG>134 North Peters Rd., 694-0500
<BR>    Authentic Indian fare for every palate, from hot and spicy Lamb Vindaloo
to creamy Chicken Tikka Masala. The menu is user-friendly huge, with a dizzying
and exotic variety in the bread section alone. Lunch buffet Mon.-Fri.
11am-2:30pm, dinner Mon.-Fri. 5:30pm-10pm, Sat. &amp; Sun. lunch 11:30am-3pm,
dinner 6pm-10pm. $7-12. V/MC/D. Full bar.
<H2>Italian
</H2><P><STRONG>Altruda's
<BR></STRONG>125 N. Peters Road, 690-6144
<BR>    A variety of Italian pasta, veal, chicken, and seafood specialties
served
in a dimly lit, wine-cellar-like atmosphere. Very romantic. Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm. $12 and up. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Cappuccino's
<BR></STRONG>7316 Kingston Pike, 673-3422
<BR>    Continental cuisine--with emphasis on Northern Italian. Intimate
atmosphere
and impressive wine list make it the perfect place for that special occasion.
Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm. $12 and up. V/MC/AE/D/DC.
Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Catinella's Bistro and Bakery
<BR></STRONG>1031 Summerwood Rd., 670-9970
<BR>    Specialties of the house feature family recipes for baked penne,
lasagna,
calzone, smoked chicken breast and a variety of fresh-baked European breads.
Tues.-Th. 11am-9pm, Fri.-Sat. 11am-10pm,. Sun. Brunch 11:30am-2:30pm. Closed
Mondays. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC, personal checks. Beer only for sale, BYO wine.
<P><STRONG>Italian Market &amp; Grill
<BR></STRONG>9648 Kingston Pike, 690-2600
<BR>    Specializing in contemporary Italian food, the Grill has create-your-own
gourmet pizzas, salmon "Pico," pollo "Emily Anna," and other more traditional
fare in a warm atmosphere. The Sunday brunch buffet is delightful. Home cooks
will want to check out the adjacent market. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp;
Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$15. V/MC/AE/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Little Italian
<BR></STRONG>5104 Kingston Pike , 584-1204
<BR>    Italian pizzas and subs, American sandwiches and burgers, all for
the
healthy enjoyment in a comfortable non-smoking atmosphere. Mon.-Thurs. 10am-6pm,
Fri. 10am-9pm, Sat. 10am-6pm. Under $5. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Romano's Macaroni Grill
<BR></STRONG>7723 Kingston Pike, 691-0809
<BR>    It's Fine Italian food, in a rustic atmosphere "like you've never
seen
before." Specialties include shrimp saut&eacute;ed in lemon butter served
with angel hair pasta, and bowtie pasta with grilled chicken, saut&eacute;ed
onions, and cheese sauce. Voted "Best New Restaurant" by Metro Pulse readers
in 1996. Table wine run on the "honors jug system," and a full bar! Sun.-Thurs
11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC/.
<P><STRONG>Naples
<BR></STRONG>5500 Kingston Pike, 584-5033
<BR>    Traditional Northern Italian cuisine served in a romantic, intimate
Old
World atmosphere. A Knoxville classic (voted "Best Italian Restaurant" with
the "Best Romantic Atmosphere") with tantalizing daily specials. Lunch Mon.-Fri.
11am-2pm, dinner Sun.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm. Lunch under
$12, dinner $12-$18. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Savelli's
<BR></STRONG>3055 Sutherland Ave., 521-9085
<BR>    A family-style neighborhood restaurant with inexpensive, authentic
dishes.
Be sure to try the spinach lasagna. Mon. 5pm-9pm, Tues.-Thurs 11am-9pm, Fri.
&amp; Sat. 11am-10pm. Under $7. BYOB.
<P><STRONG>Tuscany Il Ristorante
<BR></STRONG>5200 Kingston Pike, 584-6755
<BR>    Under new management (translated as "new and improved"). In addition
to
their 16 varieties of homemade pasta (try the squid-ink pasta!), the menu
features new specials daily and is expanding to include more continental
cuisine. Open daily 5pm-10pm. $12 and up. V/MC/AE/DC. Wine and liquor.
<H2>Japanese
</H2><P><STRONG>Kanpai of Tokyo
<BR></STRONG>1645 Downtown W. Blvd., 693-3903
<BR>    Dinner is the entertainment at this Japanese steak house. They will
chop,
dice, saut&eacute; and season your scallops, shrimp and filet right before
your very eyes. An absolute treat. Lunch Mon.-Fri. 11:30am-2pm, Sun. 10am-2:30pm.
Dinner Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-10pm, Sun. 4:30pm-8:30pm.
$12 and up. AE/D/DC/MC/V. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Kyoto
<BR></STRONG>8207 Kingston Pike, 691-3121
<BR>    Specializing in steak and seafood hibachi-style, this entertaining
restaurant
also has an extensive sushi bar. Be sure to hit their early bird specials
for some amazingly low prices on mass quantities of Japanese food. Mon.-Thurs.
5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm, Sun. 5pm-9pm. $7-$15. V/MC/AE. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<H2>Korean
</H2><P><STRONG>Kaya Korean
<BR></STRONG>149 Montvue Rd., 691-0237
<BR>    One of the most unique Asian restaurants in town, Kaya serves authentic
Korean cuisine. That means hae mool pa jun (seafood pancake), bulkoki (barbecue),
bibim bab (marinated sea and land vegetables), and jap chae (marinated noodles).
The weekend lunch buffet is among the best in town, 12pm-3pm. Karaoke after
9pm. Lunch: Tues.-Fri. 11am-3pm, Dinner: Sun.-Sat. 5pm-10pm $7-$12. V/MC.
Beer and wine.
<H2>Lunch
</H2><P><STRONG>Applecake Tea Room
<BR></STRONG>620 Campbell Station Rd., 966-7848
<BR>    Sandwiches, salads and soups plus homemade desserts. Mon.-Sat. 11am
-
2:30pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE.
<P><STRONG>Eva's for Lunch
<BR></STRONG>Homberg Place, 558-8573
<BR>    Let's lunch. Lots of yummy quiches, cakes, pies and an especially
good
chicken and fruit salad. Get it to go or sit down and relax in a smoke-free
environment. Mon.-Fri. 11am-3pm, carryout 10:30am-4:30pm. Under $7. No credit
cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Ruffles and Truffles Tearoom
<BR></STRONG>Western Plaza, 588-0439
<BR>    Charming little stop for the Western Plaza shopper. Try their iced
spiced
tea or their homemade soups, such as Swiss tomato mushroom. Mon.-Fri. 8am-3pm.
Under $7. V/MC/AE. No alcohol.
<H2>Mediterranean
</H2><P><STRONG>Mattioda's Mediterranean
<BR></STRONG>138 West End, Farragut, 675-4787
<BR>    A primo combination of imagination and the finest ingredients make
Mattioda's
a truly fine dining experience. Chefs Dean Hoyos-Holsberry and Mark DeCoates
whip up exotic flavors in dishes ranging from fattoush and Horiatiki salad
to staples like Black Angus filet and rack of lamb. The homemade pita bread
and focaccia make the trip west worthwhile. Tues.-Sat., 5pm til 10pm, Sun.
brunch 11am-2pm. V/MC/D/AE/DC/CB. Full bar.
<H2>Mexican
</H2><P><STRONG>El Charro
<BR></STRONG>6701 Kingston Pike, 584-9807
<BR>    Mexican comfort food. The "El Charro" will keep you going for days--there
is almost one of everything in this combo dinner. Lunch Mon.-Thurs. 11am-2:30pm
and 5pm-10:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10:30pm, Sun. noon-10pm. Under $7 to
$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine. liquor at Knoxville location. In Farragut,
just beer.
<P><STRONG>Garcia's
<BR></STRONG>1516 Downtown West Blvd., 690-9910<BR>Best Mexican happy hour in town? Half off their appetizers and creatively
flavored margaritas. But do also try their spinach enchiladas, fajitas and
the black beans. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight, Sun.
11am-10pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>La Paz
<BR></STRONG>Suburban Center, 690-5250
<BR>    Nouveau Southwestern cooking in an intimate atmosphere. The Mexicotti
enchiladas, chili rellenos, and zapnins are all out of this world. Voted
Knoxville's "Best Mexican Restaurant" in our '96 Readers Poll. Mon.-Sun.
5pm-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Mexicali Rose
<BR></STRONG>6500 Kingston Pike, 588-9191
<BR>    Considered by many to be Knoxville's most authentic Mexican restaurant.
The "Lupita" made with green chili, cheese, onions, and enchiladas with beans
and lettuce will knock your socks off. Lunch Tues.-Fri. 11am-2pm, dinner
5pm-8:30pm, Sat. 5pm-8:30pm. Under $9. No credit cards. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Monterrey
<BR></STRONG>7201 Kingston Pike, 584-1453
<BR>    Inexpensive Mexican for those on a budget. They use a non-traditional
spicy tomato sauce for their burritos that is amazingly good. Lunch Mon.-Thurs.
11am-2:30pm, dinner Mon.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5pm-11pm, Sun.
11am-10pm. Under $7. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Mid-East
</H2><P><STRONG>Ali Baba's
<BR></STRONG>8361 Kingston Pike, 693-1446
<BR>    Middle Eastern fast food for the discriminating palate. Possibly
the best
hummus in town, as well as great "[fill in the blank] in a sack" sandwiches.
Mon.-Thurs. 6:30am-2am, Fri. &amp; Sat. 6:30am-4am, Sun. 10am-11pm. Under
$7. No credit cards. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Dad's Cafe
<BR></STRONG>Homberg Place, 584-2143
<BR>    Knoxville's only Lebanese restaurant. A great selection of vegetarian
dishes. The baba ganoush and lamb shish kabob are out of this world. Try
Dad's specialty dinners on the weekends. Tues.-Sat. 11am-3pm, Fri. &amp;
Sat. 5:30pm-10pm. $7-$12 and up. MC/V. BYOB.
<P><STRONG>Olive Tree
<BR></STRONG>5120 Kingston Pike, 909-0434
<BR>    Homburg Place<BR>A real taste of the Mediterranean right here at home. House specialties
are the lamb dishes, and gyros, they also offer vegetarian delights and Greek
traditionals. This family restaurant also has a bakery with fresh pita bread
and desserts made daily. If you love what you eat, everything on the menu
is available in the adjoining shop. Mon.-Sun. 10am-10pm. $3-$13. V/MC/D/DC.
No alcohol.
<H2>Pizza
</H2><P><STRONG>Pizza Chef
<BR></STRONG>10205 Kingston Pk. Suite B, 691-4999
<BR>    Gourmet pizza in Farragut. All kinds of good toppings like mandarin
oranges,
barbecued chicken, and fresh basil. AND they deliver. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm, Sun. 4pm-10pm. Under $7 and up. No credit cards.
No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Roman's Pizza
<BR></STRONG>Windsor Square, 539-1784
<BR>    A west-side favorite with many loyal followers. Try the "white pizza."
Also has other Italian basics such as lasagna, baked ziti, calzones. Mon.-Sat.
11:30am-10pm, Sun. opens "later." Under $7. Cash only. No alcohol.
<H2>Seafood
</H2><P><STRONG>Squirrely Shirley's Shrimp Shack
<BR></STRONG>8027 Kingston Pike, 539-1700
<BR>    This is a shrimp-o-rama. Try it swimming in garlic or with barbecue
sauce.
And that's not to mention all the other yummy stuff like raw oysters and
crab legs. Mon.-Thurs. 4pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10:30pm, Sun. 11am-10pm.
$5-$14. V/MC/AE/DC/D/checks. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Steak
</H2><P><STRONG>Chisolm Trail Steakhouse
<BR></STRONG>7051 Kingston Pike, 584-2001
<BR>    Skip the trip to Disneyland this year, and point the family truckster
toward Chisolm Trail for a little taste of Frontierland right here in Knoxville.
Difference is, the certified angus beefsteak is on the plate, not milling
around in a costume. Opening for lunch soon. Mon.-Thurs. 4pm-10:30pm, Fri.
&amp; Sat. 4pm-11:30pm, Sun. 3pm-10pm. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>The Chop House
<BR></STRONG>9700 Kingston Pike, 531-2467
<BR>    Meat lovers' paradise that's soon to go national. Try the Big Orange
sweet
potato--you won't regret it. Sun-Thurs. 11pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11pm-11pm.
$7 - $12 and up. V/MC/AE/. Beer and wine.
<P><STRONG>The Frontier House
<BR></STRONG>10403 Kingston Pike, 693-7210
<BR>    Specialties of this house include smoked prime and BBQ ribs, and
wonderfully
hand-pattied burgers. Check out the daily lunch specials. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $2.25-$14.00. V/MC/D. Beer only.
<P><STRONG>Longhorn Steaks
<BR></STRONG>6901 Kingston Pike, 584-9544
<BR>    Catch of the day: Cow. No frilly stuff here--this place is a STEAK
house.
Well, except for the exceptional salmon, that is. Mon.-Fri. 11am-10:30pm,
Sat. 4pm-11:30pm, Sun. noon-10:30pm. $7-$12+. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Thai
</H2><P><STRONG>Stir Fry Cafe
<BR></STRONG>7240 Kingston Pike, 588-2064
<BR>    Knoxville can't seem to get enough of this upbeat bistro, voted "Best
Asian Restaurant" by our readers for the third time. And for good reasons,
too: not only does it have a full bar and patio, but great Thai items like
Pad Thai and coconut milk soup. They also have their own unique Chinese dishes,
and a good vegetarian selection. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-10:30pm. $7-$12 V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Wings
</H2><P><STRONG>Hooter's
<BR></STRONG>8050 Kingston Pike, 694-4668
<BR>    Finger foods for the sports fanatic: wings, oysters, clams, crab
legs
and shrimp. Their wait staff is tops (wink, wink, nudge, nudge). Mon.-Thurs.
11am-12pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-1am, Sun. 1pm-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE. Beer
only.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
