<TITLE>Metro Pulse Restaurant Guide</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Front Page" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_outlying.gif" ALT="Outlying Areas" WIDTH="248" HEIGHT="32">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>Mountain Harbor Inn
<BR></STRONG>1199 Hwy. 139, Dandridge, 397-3345
<BR>This delightful inn specializes in prime rib, steaks, pasta, and char-grilled
seafood and chicken. A variety of breads and desserts all made in house.
Chef Jock Ligoi from the Tastebuds Cafe will be the guest chef this summer.
Dining room closed Jan.-March (except for private parties). Tues.-Fri.
11:30am-2:30pm, 5:30pm-9pm, Sat. 11:30am-9pm, Sun. 12am-3pm. Lunch $3.95-$9.95,
dinner $12-$18. V/MC/D/AE. BYOB.
<H2>Continental
</H2><P><STRONG>Bleu Hound Grille
<BR></STRONG>80 E. Tennessee Ave.
<BR>    Oak Ridge, 481-6101
<BR>    Sophisticated American cuisine cooked over a hickory-fired grill
and served
in a cozy, casual atmosphere. Foodies take note: it's well worth the drive.
Mon.-Fri. 11am-2:30pm and Mon.-Sat. 5:30pm-9:30pm, closed Sun. Lunch under
$7, dinner $12 and up. V/MC/D/AE/DC. Beer and wine.
<P><STRONG>Harbor Inn Restaurant
<BR></STRONG>Rt. 1, Box 562 Euchee Rd.
<BR>    Ten Mile, TN, 615-334-3630
<BR>    Fine French, Italian and other worldly cuisine. Seafood specialties
like
trout filled with shrimp and lobster make it well worth the drive. Fans should
ask about the newsletter. Dinner Thurs.-Sun. 6pm-10pm. Call for reservations.
Over $18. BYOB.
<P><STRONG>Simply D'vine
<BR></STRONG>213 Jackson Square Blvd.,
<BR>     Oak Ridge , 482-0077
<BR>    World cuisine good enough to eat even if you can't pronounce it.
Specialties
include tortellini with succarosa sauce and "Sweet Memories," a dish named
after the first couple engaged there: center-cut pork loin with chef Rick
Novy's own raisin sauce. The quiet (and apparently romantic) living room
atmosphere is the perfect spot to enjoy the live jazz and bluegrass. Lunch
Mon.-Fri. 11am-2pm, dinner Tues.-Thurs. 5pm-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 5-midnight.
$7-$18. V/MC/checks. Beer and wine only.
<H2>Italian
</H2><P><STRONG>Alexandro's Ristorante &amp; Pizzeria
<BR></STRONG>Midland Center (Alcoa), 984-2539
<BR>    Sure, it may be a drive, but where else are you going to find a genuine
Sicilian chef? Try his traditional pasta dishes, and his unique pizzas.
Mon.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. 11am-10pm, Sat. 4pm-10pm. $7-$12 and up. V/MC/AE/D.
Beer only.
<H2>Mexican
</H2><P><STRONG>The Front Porch
<BR></STRONG>2912 Hwy. 321 (Cosby), 487-2875<BR>Great Mexican food in one of the most beautiful areas of Tennessee. You
can eat enchiladas, tamales and super-creamy refried beans while listening
to fine bluegrass picking. The guacamole alone is worth the drive. Live music
Fri-Sun. Fri.-Sat. noon-10:30pm, Sun. noon-9pm. $7-$12. BYOB.
<P><HR>
</BODY></HTML>
