<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="head_rg.gif" WIDTH="411" HEIGHT="36" ALT="Restaurant Guide"><BR><A HREF="rg96s.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_full.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="hed_multiple.gif" ALT="Multiple Locations" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="32">
<H2>American
</H2><P><STRONG>Applebee's
</STRONG><BR>6928 Kingston Pike, 588-0766
<BR>261 N. Peters Rd., 531-5819
<BR>3216 Mall Road Circle, 523-2600
<BR>5316 Central Ave. Pike, 689-3300
<BR>Standard American fare served in a convivial gathering-place atmosphere.
Menu includes some tasty, vegetarian-friendly dishes. Sun.-Sat. 11am-2am.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Bob Evans
<BR></STRONG>211 N. Cedar Bluff, 690-3739
<BR>5604 Merchants Blvd., 689-8555
<BR>Breakfast all day and traditional home-style staples, with special menus
for seniors and children, and weekday breakfast and lunch specials. Sun.-Thurs.
6am-10pm, Fri.-Sat. 6am-11:30pm, MC/V, No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Darryl's
<BR></STRONG>6604 Kingston Pike, 584-1879
<BR>5616 Merchants Ctr. Blvd., 688-1792
<BR>Barbecue (a specialty) and more. The most succulent fried mushrooms
imaginable. Zany atmosphere--where else in town can you eat in an elevator?
Mon.-Thurs. 11am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight, Sun 10am-midnight.
$7 - $12. V/MC/AE/DC/ CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Grady's Goodtimes
<BR></STRONG>6741 Kingston Pike, 584-4663
<BR>318 N. Peters Rd., 694-4663
<BR>High-quality, heart-smart American fare in an intimate, relaxing atmosphere.
This Knoxville original has recently returned to its original menu. Be sure
not to miss their famous (infamous?) chocolate bar cake. Yum! Sun.-Thurs.
11am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-midnight. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer, wine,
liquor.
<P><STRONG>O'Charley's
<BR></STRONG>1915 Cumberland Ave., 525-7665
<BR>8029 Kingston Pike, 693-2322
<BR>117 Cedar Lane , 689-2870
<BR>Yummy after-hours appetizers and late-night late patio fun. Good salads
and sandwiches for lunch. Try their roast beef or fresh seafood specials
for dinner. Special lunch deals for the cost-conscious. Mon.-Sat. 11am-3am,
Sun. 11am-10pm. Lunch under $7, dinner $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Patrick Sullivan's
<BR></STRONG>100 N. Central, 522-4511
<BR>7545 Northshore Dr., 694-9696
<BR>Meals of the Irish pub variety. Blue-plate specials feature homemade
mashed
potatoes and fresh veggies. Wonderful turn-of-the-century saloon atmosphere
in the Old City. Old City hours Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-midnight. West location hours closes at 11pm Fri. &amp; Sat. Both locations
closed Sunday. $7-$12. V/MC/D/AE/DC/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Ruby Tuesday's
<BR></STRONG>East Towne Mall, 524-1237
<BR>West Town Mall, 690-3737
<BR>All-American menu featuring beef and chicken dishes, plus homemade soups
and an extensive salad bar. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm.
$7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>BBQ
</H2><P><STRONG>Calhoun's
<BR></STRONG>400 Neyland Dr., 673-3355
<BR>       10020 Kingston Pike , 673-3444
<BR>       While you're enjoying the delicious barbecued ribs that were voted
"Best
Ribs" in Knoxville in our '96 Readers Poll (for the second year in a row),
take in the fabulous river front view (or lakefront view, or, well, interstate
view). Don't miss such instant Knoxville classics as spinach Maria, white
bean chili, and the original onion loaf. Mon.-Fri. 11am-10pm, Sat.-Sun.
11am-11pm. $7-$17. V/MC/AE/DC/D/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Burgers
</H2><P><STRONG>Bel Air Grill
<BR></STRONG>9117 Executive Park Dr.	694-0606
<BR>       3802 Neal Dr. (in Halls)	922-5522
<BR>       2650 Airport Hwy. (in Alcoa)	981-3788
<BR>       Burgers, shakes, fries and other authentic throw-back '50s fare.
If '90s
fare is more your style, try the steaks and chicken. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12+. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine coolers.
<H2>Chinese
</H2><P><STRONG>Lotus Garden
<BR></STRONG>460 N. Cedar Bluff Rd., 690-5788
<BR>       131 Forks of the River Parkway (Sevierville), 453-3891
<BR>       In addition to a full a la carte menu, Lotus Garden boasts an
extensive
lunch and dinner buffet that features such normally high-dollar entrees as
General Chow's Chicken and Sesame Chicken, fresh and hot (and cheap!).
Sun.-Thurs. 11am-9:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-10pm. Lunch under $7, dinner
under $12. V/MC/AE/D. No alcohol.
<H2>Continental
</H2><P><STRONG>Copper Cellar
<BR></STRONG>1807 Cumberland Ave., 673-3411
<BR>    7316 Kingston Pike , 673-3422
<BR>    Steak and seafood specialty house that's once again a Best of Knoxville
winner for "Best Sunday Brunch." They're also proud of their prime rib and
seafood specialties. The campus location boasts the happeningest happy hour
in town. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10:30pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11:30pm, Sun. 11am-10pm.
$7-$15. V/MC/AE/DC/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Deli
</H2><P><STRONG>Blimpie Express
<BR></STRONG>9541 Kingston Pike, 539-0518
<BR>    7701 Northshore Dr., 690-4378
<BR>    8410 Middlebrook Dr., 470-4849
<BR>    It's the place to go when you want a sub, and want it fast. Catering
to
the those on the run, they offer a variety of subs and salads. Havin' a party?
Order a 3-foot-sub, or a 6-foot depending on how much your friends eat. Sun.-Sat.
9am-10pm. Cash only. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>New York Bagel Shop &amp; Delicatessen
<BR></STRONG>4622 Kingston Pike, 588-1364
<BR>    710 S. Gay St. , 546-7777
<BR>    An inventive menu of the kitchen's own sandwich creations, plus scads
of ingredients with which you can dream up your own Dagwood. Bagel-wise,
they'll deck yours out with anything from bacon and chive cream cheese to
PB &amp; J. Voted "Best Bagel Shop" by our readers. Kingston Pike: Mon.-Sat.
6 am-9pm, Sun. 7am-6pm, Gay St.: Mon.-Fri.: 6:30am-5:30pm, closed weekends.
Under $4. No credit cards. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Nixon's Deli
<BR></STRONG>5034 N. Broadway, 281-8435
<BR>    East Towne Mall, 525-3343
<BR>    5716 Kingston Pike, 558-6354
<BR>    4423 Western Ave., 637-6104
<BR>    220 N. Peters Rd., 694-3719
<BR>    West Town Mall, 691-8581
<BR>    Nixon's features Lay's deli meats, including ham and turkey that
are almost
fat-free for your heart-smart munching pleasure. They also offer several
meat-free sandwiches. Mon.-Sat. 10am-midnight, Sun. 11am-9pm. Under $7. No
credit cards. No alcohol.
<H2>Family
</H2><P><STRONG>Denny's
<BR></STRONG>118 Merchants Dr., 689-6092
<BR>    220 N. Cedar Bluff Rd., 691-1680
<BR>    Nocturnal nutrition for the over-the-road truck driver or wayward
barfly
with a growling stomach, Denny's breakfasts and dinner entrees are all available
24 hours a day. Under $7. V/MC/D/AE. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Great American Steak &amp; Buffet Co.
<BR></STRONG>900 Merchants Dr. , 687-8773
<BR>    4310 Chapman Hwy., 579-6002
<BR>    It's the mother of all buffets, with tables upon tables laden with
many
food items: shrimp, roast beef, potato casserole, grilled chicken, steak
and a salad bar. Don't forget to ask for a baked sweet potato with brown
sugar and cinnamon. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12.
V/MC/AE. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Morrison's Cafeteria
<BR></STRONG>3052 East Towne Mall, , 522-5952
<BR>    Foothills Mall, Maryville , 982-8811
<BR>    Where the blue-plate special is alive and well. Green beans and lima
beans
for all with a corn muffin on the side. Mon.-Sat. 11am-8:30pm, Sun. 11am-7pm.
V/MC/AE/D. Local checks only. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Quincy's Family Steakhouse
<BR></STRONG>4725 N. Broadway, 688-9848
<BR>    Real food for real people. Food bar aside, Quincy's will fix your
meat
and potatoes any way you like 'em. Sun.-Thurs. 11am-9pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-10pm. $7-$12 V/MC/AE. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>S &amp; S Cafeteria
<BR></STRONG>9381 Kingston Pk., 694-6005
<BR>    4808 Kingston Pk., 584-5191
<BR>    A real cafeteria, with sliding trays, steam table and the works,
got them
voted #1 in our readers poll. Perfect spot for dinner or Sunday brunch. Open
from 11am-8:30pm daily. Under $7. V/MC/AE/D. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Shoney's
<BR></STRONG>4032 N. Broadway, 687-5432
<BR>    2612 Chapman Hwy., 573-4514
<BR>    5420 Clinton Hwy., 687-4282
<BR>    8529 Walker Springs Rd., 693-4411
<BR>    4410 Western Ave., 525-2242
<BR>    401 Lovell Rd., 966-2856
<BR>    Yeah, sure, they've got lots of quick, affordable entrees, but we
all
know what they're famous for: the FOOD BAR. Who knows what delights you might
find there? Sun.-Thurs. 6am-midnight, Fri. &amp; Sat. 6am-2am. Under $7.
V/MC/AE/D. No alcohol.
<H2>Italian
</H2><P><STRONG>Olive Garden
<BR></STRONG>7206 Kingston Pike, 584-7300
<BR>    201 Cedar Lane, 689-1980
<BR>    Homemade pasta, pasta fagioli and all-you-can eat salads with
breadsticks.
Sun.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-11pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D/DC. Beer,
wine, liquor.
<H2>Lunch
</H2><P><STRONG>Ham 'N Goody's
<BR></STRONG>606 W. Main Avenue, 637-2636
<BR>    314 Northshore Dr., 584-2246
<BR>    9724 Kingston Pike, 531-7488
<BR>    Let us explain. First Ham: spiral-sliced honey-baked ham served on
homemade
honey-wheat bread. Then 'N Goody's: a wide variety of deliciously sinful
baked goods made in the on-site bakery. Mon.-Fri. 8:30am-2:30pm. Under $7.
V/MC/PC. No alcohol.
<H2>Mexican
</H2><P><STRONG>Cancun
<BR></STRONG>4409 Chapman Hwy., 577-8881
<BR>    4829 N. Broadway, 688-4030
<BR>    7355 Kingston Pike, 588-6459
<BR>    Authentic homestyle Mexican. Some interesting concoctions such as
the
carne asada or the chili Colorado. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-10pm, Fri. &amp; Sat.
11am-11pm, Sun. Noon-11pm. Under $7-$12. V/MC/AE/DC/D. Beer, wine, liquor.
<P><STRONG>Chili's Grill &amp; Bar
<BR></STRONG>7304 Kingston Pike, 584-8195
<BR>    120 W. Mabry Hood Rd., 470-8664
<BR>    Affordable, dependable Tex-Mex served in a boisterous, family-friendly
atmosphere. Try the delicious fajitas, veggie tacos, burgers or the Frisco
salad. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-11pm, Fri.-Sat. 11am-midnight, Sun. 11am-10:30pm.
Under $12. V/MC/AE/D/DC/CB. Beer, wine, liquor.
<H2>Pizza
</H2><P><STRONG>Papa John's
<BR></STRONG>811 S. 22nd St., 522-7272
<BR>    402 N. Cedar Bluff, 690-7272
<BR>    4749 N. Broadway, 281-7272
<BR>    5617 Western Ave., 546-7272
<BR>    7000 Kingston Pk., 584-7272
<BR>    10820 Kingston Pk. (Farragut), 675-7272
<BR>    You call them, they bring pizza right to your door. It doesn't get
any
easier than that. Be sure to add an order of those breadsticks we all love,
too. Go ahead, get crazy, ask for the garlic sauce. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-11pm,
Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-12 midnight. Sunday noon-11pm. Under $12. No credit
cards. Checks accepted. No alcohol.
<P><STRONG>Stefano's
<BR></STRONG>1937 Cumberland Ave., 522-4151
<BR>    7213 Kingston Pike, 588-1841
<BR>    Cedar Bluff Center, 539-0033
<BR>    Chicago-style pizza featuring a healthy whole-wheat crust. Specialty
pizzas
include spicy chicken pizatone, pizza Roma, and vegetarian supreme. If you
can't come in for a slice, they were voted "Best Delivered Pizza" in our
'96 readers poll. Mon.-Thurs. 11am-11pm, Fri. &amp; Sat. 11am-12:30pm, Sun.
noon-11pm. Under $12 V/MC/AE/PC. Beer only.
<H2>Steak
</H2><P><STRONG>Outback Steakhouse
<BR></STRONG>330 N. Peters Rd., 539-2540
<BR>    314 Merchants Dr., 281-0999
<BR>    Standard steakhouse enlivened by its Australian theme--expect Down
Under
schtick on the walls and on the menu. But the food is no joke. And try out
the coconut shrimp as an appetizer--yow! Mon.-Thurs. 4:30pm-10:30pm, Fri.
4pm-11:30pm, Sat. 3:30pm-11:30pm, Sun. 3pm-10pm. $7-$12. V/MC/AE/D. Beer,
wine, liquor.
