<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Egos-A-Go-Go</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"><P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../../index.shtml"><IMG ALIGN=Middle  SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_home.gif" ALT="Staff Directory" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../zine.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_zine.gif" ALT="The 'Zine" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../suncity.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_suncity.gif" ALT="Sunsphere City" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<A HREF="../../market.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_market.gif" ALT=" Marketplace" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A> 
<A HREF="../../bonus.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_bonus.gif" ALT="Bonus Track" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1"></A>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG SRC="hed_egos.gif" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="27" ALT="Egos-A-Go-Go">

<H2><IMG SRC="egos.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50" HEIGHT="72" ALT="Egos-A-Go-Go">In days of old...</H2>
...the average person with something to say had to resort to a photocopier and the U.S. Postal Service to publish thoughts, visions, questionable conspiracy theories, and photos of award-winning tomato plants.
<P>Those days are over. With nothing more than a basic grasp of HTML and space on a web server, countless people have made their lives as they see them available for global consumption. What drives otherwise calm, rational people to reveal their life details to anyone with an Internet connection? We'll leave that one up to an aspiring sociology Master's candidate and simply present a list of those who have their own web pages. This way, perhaps you can get to know your fellow Knoxvillians on a more personal basis, thus adding further tranquility to our community.
<P>If you: 1) live in Knoxville, 2) have a personal (<STRONG>not</STRONG> commercial!) web page, and 3) would like it listed here, send a note to our webmonkey (<A HREF="mailto:jojo@metropulse.com">jojo@metropulse.com</A>).

<P>
