<IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="subhead_guidelines.gif" ALT="Calendar Submission Guidelines"><BR>
<A HREF="../calendar_dir/calendar.html"><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="../../graphics_misc/b_calendar.gif" ALT="Calendar" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="1" VSPACE="3"></A>
<P><IMG ALIGN=Middle SRC="read_or_die.gif" ALT="Read or die!" WIDTH="117" HEIGHT="14" HSPACE="10">
<P><EM>Last updated 1.29.96</EM>
<P><STRONG>Listings are free.</STRONG>
<H3>Deadlines
</H3><P>Metro Pulse is published every Thursday. Deadline for the Metro Pulse
events calendar is Monday, ten days before publication. Press releases that
come in after this date will be considered only as space permits.
<H3>How to submit listings
</H3><P>Listings are preferred in writing and are accepted through the following
routes:
<P><STRONG>Snail mail:</STRONG> Metro Pulse, Attn: Calendar, 505 Market
St., Suite 300,
Knoxville, 37902
<BR><STRONG>Fax:</STRONG> (423) 522-2955, Attn: Calendar
<BR><STRONG>E-mail:</STRONG>
<A HREF="mailto:metroshel@aol.com">metroshel@aol.com</A>
<P>Listings may also be submitted in writing in person. Please do not
submit listings by phone.
<P>Listings are divided into the following categories, and should contain
the following information:
<P><STRONG>Music:</STRONG> band name, brief description (if available), venue,
time, cover
charge. Please also note if the show is all ages, 18+, or 21+.
<P><STRONG>Dance Clubs:</STRONG> venue, phone number, date and time, brief
description.
<P><STRONG>Theater and Dance:</STRONG> event title, venue name and address,
brief description
(if you wish), show dates, time, ticket price, and phone number to order
tickets or phone number of venue.
<P><STRONG>Art: </STRONG>venue, address, phone number, hours of operation,
show dates, title
of exhibit, artist's name, brief description (if you wish).
<P><STRONG>Open Call:</STRONG> Includes theater audition notices, call for
artists, and volunteer
opportunities: name of sponsor group, date or deadline, venue (if applicable),
time (if applicable), brief description or explanation, phone number or address.
<P><STRONG>Open Book:</STRONG> Includes lectures and book-signings: name
of author or speaker,
date, venue, time, admission price, brief description, book title (if
applicable), phone number.
<P><STRONG>Kids:</STRONG> please include info for date, time, any fees,
and phone number.
<P><STRONG>Sports:</STRONG> name of teams, dates, venue, time.
<P><STRONG>Classes/Workshops:</STRONG> please include info for date, time,
any fees, brief
description of class, instructor's name, and a phone number.
<P><STRONG>Events:</STRONG> This is our miscellaneous category. Please include
whatever info
is applicable, including date, time, venue, price, a brief description of
the event, and a phone number.
<P><STRONG>Meetings:</STRONG> Meetings must be in the public interest and
not for private
profit. Please include name of group, brief description (if you wish), date,
time, venue, phone number.
<P><STRONG>Incomplete listings will not be accepted.</STRONG>
<H3>General policies
</H3><P>Calendar information is compiled from what is specifically addressed
to
the calendar. Do not assume that information listed in an ad or elsewhere
in the publication will automatically make it into the calendar. Metro Pulse
is not responsible for missing information if it is not submitted to the
calendar editor.
<P>Continuing information (info without a specific end date) for meetings
or music must be updated every twelve weeks, or it will be removed from the
calendar.
<P>Listings can run for two issues prior to the event, or the event's
registration deadline, space permitting.
<P>TBAs will not be listed in the music calendar unless specifically requested.
<P>Classes/Workshop listings are accepted for date-specific events ONLY.
The calendar is not an advertising vehicle for ongoing businesses.
<P>Listing submissions for out-of-town events are considered only as space
permits, no exceptions.
<P>Unfortunately, due to lack of space, we are not able to accept listings
for high school, junior high or elementary theater performances.
<P>Sales, or "sales events," are not considered calendar information and
will not be promoted in the calendar under any circumstances.
<P>Metro Pulse is not responsible for incorrect calendar information unless
we have received a press release, on paper, containing the correct information.
